title: sugar cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make stiff.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients in an ungreased square 8 x 8 baking pan.
Make three wells in the mixture.
Pour vanilla into first well, vinegar into second well and vegetable oil into third well.
Pour water over the entire mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
It is extra special when garnished with a dollop or two of whipped chocolate frosting (recipe below).
Note: Double all amounts if using 9 x 13 baking pan.

title: smoked eggs
directions: Hard-boil eggs; peel.
Run a thin skewer through eggs from top to bottom and side to side.
Heat water and remaining ingredients to a boil.
Put eggs in a jar.
Pour boiling liquid over eggs. Cover.
When cool, refrigerate 24 hours.
Shake and refrigerate at least 6 hours more.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows over bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine thawed berries and jello; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour batter over marshmallows.
Spoon strawberry mixture over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tuna fish snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on small toasted rounds or squares of bread.
Brush with melted butter.
Place under broiler until golden brown.
Makes 24 snacks.

title: beef stew(serves 4)
directions: Brown meat in oil in skillet.
Transfer meat to 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine all other ingredients; mix with meat. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Good served over hot biscuits.

title: lime molded salad
directions: Mix sugar, pineapple juice and water in small pan.
Boil until sugar dissolves.
Remove from water; add jello.
Cool until slightly jelled.
Whip cream.
Add cottage cheese, jello mixture and crushed pineapple.
Mold.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo and flour or graham cracker crumbs.
Press in 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.
If using flour, bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
(Don't bake if using graham cracker crumbs.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Cook as normal cornbread.
May rinse corn can with small amount of water, if mixture is too dry; however, the mixture should be a little thick.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and ground pecans together and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Grease cookie sheet.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut and boil squash.
Saute onion in butter.
Premix other ingredients in a separate container.
Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in greased casserole dish.

title: streusel filled coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift dry ingredients together. Cut in shortening. Mix in egg, which has been beaten with milk and vanilla. Pour into pan. Top with Streusel.

title: rice stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Cut peppers in half and place in boiling water; remove from heat immediately and let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix beef, rice, salt, pepper, onion and 1 can tomato sauce.
Place mixture in peppers.
Combine other can of tomato sauce and sour cream and pour over stuffed peppers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: toasted tuna sandwiches
directions: Combine tuna, celery, green pepper, relish, lemon juice, mayo and cheese.
Spread evenly on 6 slices bread and cover with remaining slices.
Combine eggs and milk.
Melt butter in skillet. Dip sandwiches in egg mixture.
Turn so both sides are coated. Cook sandwiches until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Put cherries in pan and smooth out. Put pineapple on top. Sprinkle sugar on top evenly. Spread cake mix on top. Pour melted butter on top and sprinkle pecans on top.

title: amaretto
directions: Simmer sugar, water and lemon peel 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Add vodka, almond, vanilla and chocolate flavoring.
Remove lemon peel.
Yields 1 1/2 fifths; cooled Amaretto can be poured into 2 bottles.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place 4 pork chops in bottom of baking dish.
Salt and pepper the chops.
Place carrots, potatoes and onion on top of chops. Pour over this 1 can cream of mushroom soup plus 1/2 can of water. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice and chicken
directions: Season chicken with paprika, garlic salt and celery salt. Place chicken skin side up in greased shallow 2 1/2-quart baking dish or 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Push chicken to one side.
Add rice, onion, peppers and parsley. Combine remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over rice mixture; stir well.
Arrange chicken on rice.
Cover and continue baking 30 minutes longer or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: grandma's sugar cookies(1920)
directions: Roll out and sprinkle sugar on them.
Bake at 350° about 12 minutes.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar, amount depending on rhubarb tartness and your taste buds.
Mix lightly with rhubarb; place in pie shell and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust with slits cut in it or make lattice work top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes until juice begins to bubble through slits.
Serve warm.

title: calabacitas con pollo
directions: Chop chicken into bite size pieces.
Brown in a Dutch oven with a little olive oil.
Add onion and garlic, stirring until onion begins to get a little limp.
Add squash, corn, tomatoes, comino, salt and pepper.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until chicken and squash are done.

title: marinated grilled flank steak
directions: Marinate flank steak several hours, then grill.
Slice thin on diagonal to serve.

title: herb bread
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Add water, parsley, shortening and herbs.
Beat and add the remaining flour.
Add more flour, if needed.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for 40 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place leaves and garlic into food processor.
Blend.
Add oil (may freeze at this point) or add nuts and cheese.
Use with spaghetti, linguini or add tablespoon to soups.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Quarter carrots and cut into 1/2-inch pieces; set aside with onion and mushrooms.
Coat a nonstick skillet with oil and brown chicken on both sides, after salt and peppering; set aside.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll out for 2 pie crusts.
Use for pies such as tourtiere or fruit pies.

title: pineapple-cranberry freeze
directions: Drain pineapple.
Put the juice in a bowl.
Slice bananas lengthwise and then cut into pieces.
Put the pieces in pineapple juice.

title: red apple coleslaw
directions: Core and chop red apples without paring.
Mix all ingredients with salad dressing to which cream has been added.
Heap in crisp lettuce cups and garnish with walnut halves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello in 3/4 cup hot water.
Let stand for a few minutes. Add Pet milk and all other ingredients; mix well and pour in desired mold.

title: maid-rites
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook over medium heat for at least 1 hour, the longer the better.

title: holiday mints
directions: Mix all ingredients and mold.
These can be colored pastel colors or whatever color you need for baby showers, wedding showers, anniversary and etc.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pineapple juice, eggs and 2 chopped pineapple rings.
Blend until smooth.
Melt butter in skillet over medium-low heat. Add brown sugar and stir to dissolved.
Arrange 8 pineapple rings in bottom of skillet. Place a cherry in center of each ring.

Pour batter evenly into skillet. Cover and heat until cover is hot to touch, about 4 to 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low or simmer and bake 15 to 20 minutes until cake is done. Turn out onto a large plate.

title: oven baked apple pancakes with sausage
directions: Brown sausage.
Combine ingredients.
Add apples.
Pour into greased 10 x 6-inch pan.
Put sausage on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with syrup.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Brown flour in oil until copper color. Add 1 cup onions. Add to water a bag of crab boil and let come to a boil. Remove bag and add roux, bay leaves, remaining onions, celery, garlic and bell pepper. Let simmer for 1 hour. Then add Ro-Tel tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings. Let simmer another 30 minutes. Add shrimp, green onions and parsley. Let boil until shrimp are cooked, about 3 to 5 minutes. Add 1 tablespoon file. Remove bay leaves. Serve over rice.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook sauce for 2 hours; then add shredded meat and simmer. Serves 12 people.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together cooked spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese. Place mixture in baking pan and spread evenly.
Spread Ricotta cheese as evenly as possible over spaghetti mixture.

title: cajun chew cake
directions: Mix together sugar, butter and beaten eggs.
Mix flour, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into well-greased, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: johnny apple cakes
directions: Mix well and fry like pancakes.
Enjoy!

title: quick apple dessert
directions: Place apples in a buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle gelatin over apples.
Combine flour and sugar in small bowl.
Cut margarine in until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed and drain.
Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add stuffing mix to sauteed onions.
Mix eggs, spinach and garlic powder and add to stuffing-butter mixture.
Roll into walnut-size balls and freeze on cookie sheet.
Keep frozen in plastic bag until ready to bake.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Watch carefully; balls should be firm (not mushy).

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in whole wheat flour; blend.
Beat together egg, milk and oil in a 4-cup measure.
Add to dry ingredients.
Heat griddle with butter.
Add batter.
Makes about 8 pancakes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onions.
Mix the butter and stuffing together.
Put half of the squash mix in a casserole dish and half of the stuffing mix, then the rest of the squash and end with stuffing topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
beef
and cook onion, garlic
and
oregano.
Add soup, water and vinegar.	Simmer 30 minutes,
stirring now and then.
In baking dish or cake pan, arrange in alternate layers of
noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce	and
Mozzarella.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes. Serves 6.

title: scrambled eggs casserole
directions: Soak bread cubes in milk; set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp. Drain and crumble; set aside.
Thaw egg substitute and scramble lightly in butter just until set.
Add bread cubes to eggs and scramble until all ingredients are combined.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over egg mixture and top with cheese.
Saute bread crumbs in additional butter until brown.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and crumbled bacon over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion in large pan for 3 minutes.
(Do not drain.)
Add Minute rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add butter and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Heat soy sauce mixture, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour over pork.
Cover and chill 4 to 8 hours, turning meat occasionally.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix together until dough forms.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft at 400° (8 to 10 minutes).

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line bottom of pan with whole crackers.
Mix pudding and milk; beat at medium speed until thick. Fold in Cool Whip; mix until blended.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers then the rest of the pudding mixture.
Top with a layer of whole crackers.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix well and freeze using muffin cups and tins.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Whisk together and chill until time to serve.

title: "english" custard
directions: Begin to heat the milk in a nonstick saucepan.
Mix cornstarch with a small amount of milk, to form a thick paste.
With a wooden spoon, mix the warm milk and cornstarch.
Keep stirring until mixture thickens.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Serve over apple pie or as desired.
Add to dessert pies for a delicious "hot" sauce.
Also good chilled.

title: madrid twists
directions: In small mixer bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Mix in egg, egg yolk and orange peel.
Reserve egg white.
Gradually stir in flour and salt just until mixed.
With hands, form dough into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Divide dough into quarters.
Work with one quarter at a time; keep remaining refrigerated.
Cut each quarter into 12 pieces.
Roll each on lightly floured surface into 5-inch rope.
Place on cookie sheet and bend in the middle, then twist one end tightly around the other.
Brush with beaten egg white. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen, about 40 calories each.

title: turkey hash
directions: Melt butter. Add onion and green pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and black pepper.
When well blended, slowly add stock made from turkey bones.
Add cream, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in turkey and heat.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Simmer celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and mix well.
Add Stove Top dressing and mix.
Pat in 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Drain and layer onto dressing.
Add chicken.
Mix mushroom soup and milk (can use soup can to measure).
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle with parsley. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.

title: sesame wafers
directions: Bring margarine and cheese to room temperature to soften. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 3 logs and refrigerate until firm.
Slice and bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix sugar with shortening and salt.
Add egg.
Beat with electric mixer 1 minute or until well blended.
Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Add flour, then milk-yeast mixture and vanilla to dough batter.
Mix 3 minutes with electric mixer (use dough hook if available).
Turn dough out on floured board and knead for 1 minute.
Place in a lightly greased bowl; cover with a towel and set in a warm place to rise for 1 hour.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix first four	ingredients
together.	Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Preheat
oven
to
balls
in baking dish and pour tomato
sauce over the meat balls.
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook eggplant.
Mix with other ingredients except cracker crumbs.
Place in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the fine cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour.
If planning to freeze casserole, bake about 45 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Pour liquid over veggies and chill overnight.
You can use any kind of veggies you like.

title: skyline chili dip
directions: Press cream cheese thinly into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare chili according to package directions and allow to cool. Pour cooled chili over cream cheese and top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted.
Serve with taco chips.

title: versatile shepherd's pie
directions: Peel, dice, and cook potatoes in boiling salted water until soft.
Drain and cream with butter and milk.
Add cheese to taste. In a large pan, lightly fry onions, carrots, and garlic until soft and onions are transparent.
Add lamb mince (this can be frozen).
Stir until the mince is brown.
Add stock cube, herbs, and tomato puree.
Cook gently for 15-20 minutes.
Transfer to an oven-proof casserole dish using a slotted spoon to drain off excess fat.
Cover lamb mince with the creamy potatoes - sealing well at the edges - and making a rough top with a fork.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread rolls out on cookie sheet or jelly roll pan.
Pinch edges together to make 1 big crust and roll out thinner.
Bake about 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Make into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Can put nut in center.
Add chocolate chips or raisins.
Press down with a fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased pie pan (9 or 10-inch). Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork chop oven bake
directions: Combine flour and garlic salt and a dash of salt and pepper. Dip chops in mixture and brown well in 2 tablespoons melted fat (or oil), about 15 minutes per side.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a double boiler (or microwave), melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over Rice Chex and stir until all is covered.
Put the powdered sugar in a clean grocery bag; pour in the chocolate covered Rice Chex.
Close bag firmly and shake until all is coated.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and egg together well, add other ingredients and drop from spoon onto well-greased cookie pan, bake 10 or 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Butter a square 9 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch pan.
Stir into a saucepan, evaporated milk, sugar and salt.
Cook over low heat until mixture boils.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows and chocolate.
Stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 36 squares.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain juice from pineapple in a saucepan and add water.
Bring to a boil.
Add rice and salt.
Reduce heat, cover and cook until soft.
Let cool.
Fold in pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and whipped cream.
Chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Fix pudding with milk; set aside.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and melted butter.
Combine mixture with pudding; stir in Cool Whip.
Crumble cookies on top and serve.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs (one at a time). Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa.
Add half of this to first mixture.
Mix thoroughly and then add the remaining.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet 'n sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots.
When done, add onion and green pepper to hot mixture and let set a few minutes.
Remove from heat and drain. Cook remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved and is mixed. Pour over vegetables.
This can be served hot or served cold as a relish.

title: chapatis
directions: Combine salt and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Add 3/4 cup oil and mix well.
Add water little by little until dough is soft.
Knead for 5 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup flour on cutting board. Roll out a 2-inch ball of dough until it is 1/8-inch thick (size of a saucer).
Heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat for 1 minute.
Fry Chapatis 3 to 5 minutes per side until brown.
Remove from pan and drain on paper towel.
Fry remaining Chapatis.
Serve immediately or place in covered container until ready to serve.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake as directed for 2 layer cake.
Substitute milk instead of water.
Cool.
Mix Crisco, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt with mixer on high speed for 5 minutes.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat 4 minutes and spread between layer, then ice with Duncan Hines frosting.

title: sweet celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use immediately or refrigerate.

title: cream pie(double for 2 pies)
directions: Blend
sugar,
cornstarch and salt.
Slowly stir in hot milk. Cook
and
stir over boiling water until mixture thickens.	Add 1/3
of mixture to well beaten egg yolks, then stir egg yolks into custard.
Stir and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from stove; cool.
Add	butter	and
vanilla.
Pour
into pie shell.
Cover with
meringue.
May also be served with sweetened whipped cream, adding a few drops of vanilla.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and combine the two mixtures.
Fold raisins and nuts into mixture. Pour into layer pans and bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 hour or until cake leaves sides of pan.

title: too sweet for me!
directions: Mix 1 part Frosted Flakes with 1 part corn flakes, or mix to your own liking (1 Frosted to 2 corn flakes, etc.).

title: fajita nachos
directions: In a large, heavy plastic bag, mix lime juice, oil, beer, garlic, coriander, cumin and chili.
Remove 3 tablespoons marinade.
Place steak in bag and seal.
Rotate bag; set it in a large pan.
Chill for at least 2 hours or up until next day; turn occasionally.
Place meat on a grill 4 to 6 inches above a solid bed of hot coals (you can hold your hand at grill level only 2 to 3 seconds).
Grill until brown and cooked to your liking, 3 to 5 minutes per side for rare steak.
Thinly slice meat crosswise, then cut each slice in half again.

title: randy's favorite shrimp
directions: Split fresh jumbo shrimp (cleaned and headed).
Layer 1/4 sliver of jalapeno pepper and sliver of Colby cheese inside.
Wrap shrimp with piece of bacon and hold together with toothpick. Season with a little salt, if desired.
Cook for a few minutes on outdoor grill until done.

title: pecan raisin cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream shortening, add sugar and egg; one at a time; beat well after each.
Stir in nuts and raisins; add flour mixture with milk.
Beat until smooth. Add vanilla.
Bake in two pans at 375° until done or for some 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with 7 Minute Icing.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Stir in water or 7-Up and 3 tablespoons of cornstarch.
Stir in strawberry jello and sugar.
Cool for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix in bananas and fresh strawberries.

title: marinated chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle roast with tenderizer and prick with fork.
Place roast in a shallow pan. Combine the remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour marinade over roast. Cover and place in refrigerator at least 12 hours, turning at least once.
Remove the roast from the marinade and place on the grill.
Cook over hot coals for 30 to 45 minutes, basting often with marinade.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mary's homemade soup
directions: Mix ingredients in a large pot and cook until potatoes and macaroni are soft.
Good with cornbread.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice ahead of time.
Cook chicken and bell pepper in skillet with Pam or margarine until chicken is thoroughly cooked. Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan until melted.
Blend in flour and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add broth and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until bubbly, 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings (small).

title: mama mary's potato rolls
directions: Combine milk, sugar, margarine, salt and pepper in a small bowl. Cool to lukewarm.
In a large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water; set aside 5 minutes.
With whisk, beat milk mixture into mashed potato until smooth. Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour until smooth. Add additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board.
Knead about 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Add more flour as needed.
Place dough in greased bowl. Turn to expose greased portion. Cover with towel. Set aside in warm place, about 1 hour or until doubled.
Grease muffin tin. Punch down dough; divide into 12 pieces.
Shape into 2-inch balls. Cut into quarters, cutting almost through to bottom of rolls. Place each cut roll into muffin tin.
Cover and set aside in warm place to rise, 45 minutes until doubled.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients to boiling point; add butter. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening; add milk all at once.
Stir until flour is moistened.
Roll 1/4-inch thick; cut in 6-inch squares.
Place an apple on each square; season with sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Moisten the edges; fold corners to middle and pinch together.
Place dumplings 1 inch apart in baking dish.
Pour syrup over them and bake about 35 minutes at 375°.
Place cinnamon candy or cube of red jelly on top of each one.
Serve with milk or cream.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Cook all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Cool. Marinate steak, chicken or whatever for at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Can also be used for a side sauce.
Barbecue meat until done.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli-tomato pie
directions: Stir together rice and eggs in large bowl.
Melt butter in medium size saucepan.
Stir in flour; cook, stirring until smooth. Cook, stirring, until thickened and bubbly, about 2 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in broccoli, cheese, salt and pepper. Cool to lukewarm.
Stir broccoli mixture into rice. Turn into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until center almost set.
Remove from pan.
Arrange tomato slices around outer edge.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until golden.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil. Add eggs, flour, soda, salt and flavorings. In separate bowl, mix nuts, coconut and apples. Fold into creamed mixture. Bake in greased and floured pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all in a large bowl.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: saucepan scotties
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 inch quiche dish.
Bake uncovered for 40-45 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes then cut.

title: marshmallow cream icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat on high speed until it becomes very stiff.
Good to use on coconut cakes.

title: mom's round steak
directions: Place steak in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with green pepper, dry onion soup mix and tomatoes (not the juice). To the tomato juice, add the A.1. sauce and cornstarch, mixing well. Pour over steak. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake in a 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix all other ingredients. Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 325 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Mix one package of jello with water (boiling hot) and 1 cup of juice from cherries.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
All to chill until very firm.

title: baked cheese goulash
directions: In one pan, cook hamburger and onion.
In another pan, cook macaroni.
When both are done, mix together and add mushrooms and sauce.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Layer in baking pan with cheese. Completely cover with cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: zwieback pudding
directions: Roll bread to crumbs and also nuts.
Add sugar, cinnamon and melted butter.
Mix well.

title: holiday meat balls
directions: Mix ground chuck, eggs, onion, crackers, salt, pepper and parsley flakes.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: home fried potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a large frying pan and add onion.
Cut potatoes into bite size pieces or slice them to your desired thickness. Put potatoes in pan with butter and add garlic powder and pepper. Fry on medium heat until browned and tender.
Serve with breakfast, lunch or dinner.

title: graham cracker squares
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Don't let mixture sit too long in bowl.
Pour mix into well-greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown at 325°.

title: chicken chalupa casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13
inch pan, place half of crushed chips. Saute onion in margarine until tender; then add soups, milk, and picante sauce.
Cook over low heat until well blended.
Spoon half of mixture over chips, then half of chicken and half of cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: bettie mccright's italian family spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer 4 hours.
May need to add more water.
Will serve approximately 50 people.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Pull chicken off of bone and spread into a casserole dish.
Add desired amount of salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, chopped onion, milk and broth from chicken.
Pour ingredients over chicken.
Spread stuffing over top of ingredients.
Dot with butter.
Slightly moisten stuffing with broth from chicken.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef, sausage and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms; let simmer on low for 10 to 15 minutes.
In large baking dish, combine cooked noodles/beef mixture and Cheddar cheese.
Stir together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 5 minutes of baking, spread Mozzarella cheese on top.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine Hawaiian Punch, lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate, grape juice concentrate and water in large container. Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale gradually; stir. Float small scoops of sherbet on top.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 30 (5 ounce) servings.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoons into hot shortening in skillet.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Bring 2 cups water, butter and salt to a boil.
Pour rice in boiling water, simmering 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not burn.

title: french apple squares
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Blend in egg yolk and milk.
Roll out 1/2 of the dough to fit bottom of jelly roll pan. Spread with pie filling and dot with butter.
Cover with top crust and brush with egg white.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar icing.
Makes 40 (2-inch) squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Pour into well-greased 3-quart casserole.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Bake at 325° until set or knife comes out clean.

title: green chile enchiladas
directions: Cook garlic and onion in oil until tender, but do not brown. Stir in flour and broth until smooth.
Add chilies and tomatoes; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Dip tortillas, one at a time, into simmering sauce.
Remove when soft and place a large spoonful of cheese on each.
Top with a little sauce and roll.
Place in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish, seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce over and around . Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with avocado, green onion and sour cream.

title: deviled steak cubes
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge meat in flour mixture. Brown slowly on all sides in hot fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low heat for 14 to 15 hours.
Can be frozen or canned in a hot water bath.
Makes 4 pints.

title: pico de gallo(rooster's beak)
directions: Mix tomato, onion, cucumber, radishes, cilantro and peppers. Squeeze lime juice over; add salt to taste.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Makes 2 cups.

title: french dip
directions: Place roast in a slow cooker. Add water, soy sauce and seasonings. Cover and cook on high for 5 - 6 hours or until beef is tender. Remove meat from broth; thinly slice or shred and keep warm. Strain broth; skim off fat. Pour broth into small cups for dipping. Serve beef on rolls.

title: pecan coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter or honey.
Add eggs, pecans, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in shortening till red disappears.
Add onion, tomatoes, steak sauce, ketchup, green peppers and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Combine spaghetti and beef mixture in large greased baking dish and season to taste.
Fold in soup and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until top is brown.

title: muffin cheesecakes
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla and set aside.
Place 1 vanilla wafer cookie in the bottom of a paper baking cup.
(The foil ones look very nice.)
Place 1 1/2 tablespoons or so of the cream cheese mixture in each cup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
When cool, top with any flavor pie filling mixture and whipped topping. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top, if desired.
Makes 18 to 24.

title: eggplant-tomato casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Place half the sliced eggplant in a shallow oiled baking dish.
Chop the tomatoes and spoon half (with juice) over eggplant.
Place half the onion and green pepper slices over tomatoes.
Season with spices and a sprinkle of cheese.
Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Season and drizzle with a little olive oil.
Cover top with crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° until vegetables are tender.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Cook onions in butter.
Add flour, salt, mustard and milk.
Stir until thickened and smooth.
Add salt and pepper.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of carrots and cheese ending with carrots.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: basic cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter (flour or powdered sugar may be used for rolling).
These cookies can be iced for all occasions.

title: banana and peanut salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients well; add butter and cook over low heat until it begins to thicken.
Pour beaten eggs slowly into mixture and continue cooking until thick and creamy.
Cool and refrigerate.
When dressing is cold, layer in cold bowl with peanuts and sliced bananas.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add eggs, sugar, and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes, or until golden brown and cake is completely dry-looking on top.
Cool 15 minutes.
Blend sour cream, sugar, and remaining 1 teaspoon vanilla, spread evenly on cake.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Thaw strawberries and serve over cake.

title: italian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika on both sides. Lightly brown chicken in oil in frypan.
Remove chicken from pan and saute bell pepper and onion.
Add tomatoes, sugar, garlic powder and basil.
Return chicken to pan and cover.
Cook on medium heat until chicken is done.
Serve over noodles.

title: jello pudding dirt cups
directions: Pour milk in a large bowl; add Jell-O pudding mix.
Beat until well blended; let sit 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 the cookies.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cupcake pans with liners and place a vanilla wafer on the bottom of each.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Spoon into cupcake liners.
Bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Do not brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Saute chicken and onions with thyme in margarine in large skillet until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add cornstarch; stir until blended.
Stir in broth, milk, green beans, carrots, rice, salt and pepper.
Bring to full boil, stirring frequently. Simmer, covered, until rice is cooked, about 20 minutes.

title: hallelujah bread
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Sift all dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Soak fruit and nuts in the cup of wine. Add to mixture.
Put in loaf pans lined with heavy brown paper which has been greased and floured.
Bake in oven about 3 hours...Leviticus 2:4.

title: spinach ball
directions: Empty carton
of
plain
yogurt
into
cheesecloth
and suspend over
a large bowl in the refrigerator overnight.
The next day, you can
use
plain
or
added soup mix for a dip or lemon juice and honey for a salad dressing or only honey for a spread on toast.

title: cocktail biscuits
directions: Cut cheese into Bisquick; add milk.
Roll as for pastry (thin).
Cut tiny rounds; spread deviled ham between 2 rounds. Bake in a hot 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit cooler
directions: Puree the fruit with the grape juice and ice in the work bowl of a food processor or blender.
Combine in a pitcher with seltzer.
Serve in 12 ounce glasses filled with ice.
Squeeze a wedge of lemon or lime into each glass.
Makes four servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barb's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes with potato masher.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well with potato masher.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add onions and peppers. Stir in buttermilk and eggs; mix well. Add creamed corn and oil. Stir, then add cheese. Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: lye soap
directions: Dissolve lye in hot water; let cool.
Melt down beef fat; slowly pour lye mixture into melted fat.
Stir steadily until cool; pour into boxes dipped in cold water.
When cold and set, cut into bars.

title: raymond's cole slaw
directions: Combine vegetables
in	a salad bowl.
Mix sugar, salt, pepper, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Just before serving pour over vegetables and toss.
Do not add dressing ahead of time.

title: stove top cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter.
Boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet and chill.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Boil water with onion.
Add dashinamoto and saimin soup mixes. Diagonally chop vegetables. Add carrots and broccoli stalks.
Add sesame oil and garlic.
Simmer for a few minutes, then add broccoli tops, fish cake and saimin noodles. Serve with egg rolls or wonton.

title: izena dip
directions: Mix together and use it for fresh vegetables.

title: pizza in a crescent
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press to form four 7 x 5-inch rectangles, sealing perforations.

title: creole squash
directions: Cook chopped bacon in skillet 5 minutes; add onion and cook 7 minutes or until lightly brown.
Add squash and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients, except artichokes.
For every 2 artichokes, use 1 onion, 1/4 cup cheese, 2 tablespoons oil and 2 cloves of garlic.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bring large pot of water to a boil. Add pasta and cook 8 to 10 minutes. Drain and cool. In large bowl, mix eggs, Ricotta, half the Mozzarella and 1/2 the Parmesan, parsley and pepper. In medium bowl, mix pasta sauce, mushrooms and other half of the 2 cheeses. Stuff shells with Ricotta mixture. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Pour sauce mixture over shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blender pie
directions: Blend everything except coconut on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle coconut on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla
wafer crumbs and milk alternately to creamed mixture. Fold in coconut and pecans.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Addition of a ham bone adds real color and flavor not possible to achieve otherwise.
Most Cajun cooks like to boil for a couple of minutes, then let them soak in that same water overnight.
In the morning, brown sausage or fat meat first to remove some of the grease.
Bring beans to a boil again and add all other ingredients. Reduce heat and simmer for at least 3 hours.
Beans should become very creamy.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.

title: square bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add water (consistency of biscuit dough).
Roll out dough about 1/2-inch squares.
Cut hole in center.
Fry in deep fat.

title: joyce's potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and chilies. Pour into casserole pan. Dot with butter.
Cover with slivered almonds and heat at 350° until butter melts.
Yummy.

title: oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from fire and quickly add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon out onto waxed paper.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Whip cream; set aside.
Whip cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, cranberry and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream. Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting. Blend dry ingredients; stir in.
Mix in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: low-fat broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli and onion together; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and bake 20 minutes at 300°.
Casserole has 6 fat grams.

title: mulligan casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and cook until tender.
Place sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients. Bake covered in 350° oven until potatoes are tender, approximately 1 hour.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Put sliced cukes in bowl.
Add salt and let stand for 35 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cukes. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: red apples
directions: Melt red hots candy in water.
Add sugar and apples. Cook down until it jells.
Cook on medium heat.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, milk and baking powder.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 pan.
Pour peaches and juice over batter.
Add cinnamon and a little sugar over the top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lewie king's famous eggs fondue
directions: Cut crust off the bread and cube.
Grease casserole; spread half of cubed bread on bottom of casserole.
Put the browned sausage over bread and half of the cheese, then the rest of the bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and remaining cheese.
Pour over top and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, crumble cornflakes over the top.
Drizzle butter and place casserole in a pan with water and bake for 40 minutes at 400° (2-quart casserole).
Do not cover.

title: momsie's corn pudding
directions: Cut corn from cob (may use whole kernel frozen or canned corn).
Add butter, flour and seasonings.
Beat eggs together until light; add to mixture.
Pour into a buttered baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm, like custard.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix together in bowl first 4 ingredients.
When well blended add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Combine sugar and mashed potatoes.
Slightly beat eggs, milk, melted butter, nutmeg, flour and baking powder.
Mix all ingredients together.
Deep fry in Crisco oil until golden brown.

title: strawberry magic
directions: Mix lemon juice and Eagle Brand milk.
Add strawberries.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Layer vanilla wafers and this mixture in pan and top with Cool Whip.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat garlic gently in olive oil for about 5 minutes.
In shallow 9 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange vegetables in alternating layers as follows: Layer half potatoes, zucchini, tomatoes and cheese and sprinkle with herbs and salt and pepper.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with garlic and oil mixture and bake 45 minutes, uncovered.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: veal balls
directions: Shape into balls and brown in shortening or butter.
Place in casserole. Add 1 can mushroom soup and 1 can of water.
Add a little flour.
A little Kitchen Bouquet may be added.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: velveeta salsa dip
directions: In saucepan, stir together process cheese spread and salsa over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Stir in cilantro.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or broiled green, red or yellow pepper wedges, if desired.
Makes 3 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda, then mix together with rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Put into a well-greased tube pan and bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: fourteen carat cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift together first 5 ingredients. In a separate bowl, beat eggs with a wire whisk. Add sugar and beat until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients, mix well. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9 inch cake pans. Bake 35 - 40 minutes, until done. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Invert onto racks to cool completely.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Combine applesauce, sugar, oil, eggs and milk.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into applesauce mixture and beat well. Fold in pecans.
Put in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute bell pepper and onion in butter. Add seasonings and tomatoes. Add steak and let simmer until steak is done.
Add mushroom soup.
Let simmer. Serve over rice.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown floured meat in separate skillet.
In slow cooking pot, combine browned beef, bay leaf, Worcestershire, onion, bouillon, pepper, salt, sugar and vegetables.
Pour water all over.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
Turn control on high.
Thicken with leftover flour dissolved in small amount of water.
Cover and cook on high for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender until smooth, scraping sides down occasionally.

title: barbara's pork chops
directions: Line baking pan with aluminum foil.
Lightly salt and pepper chops.
Cover chops with Worcestershire sauce.
Broil on 1 side approximately 10 minutes (use top rack in oven).
Pour dripping into frying pan.
Cover other side of chops with more Worcestershire sauce and brown about 5 minutes.
Pour these drippings into pan also and add mushroom soup.
Bring this to a boil and add chops.
Turn down to a low temperature and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Delicious!
Use with homemade mashed potatoes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix together first four ingredients and pat into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Warm chocolate chips and peanut butter together.
Frost bars with this mixture and cut into squares before completely cooled.

title: pineapple fruit bowl
directions: Slice each pineapple in half lengthwise.
Using a grapefruit knife, carefully remove pineapple from shells.
Reserve shells; cut pineapple into chunks.
Combine pineapple chunks, watermelon balls, cantaloupe balls, orange sections, grapes and bananas; blend in orange juice.
Chill about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve in pineapple shells.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except onions, until well blended. Slice onions into 1/2 inch rounds; separate into rings. Dip onions in batter and deep fry until golden brown.

title: wildly delicious turkey salad
directions: Combine water and rice and seasoning packets.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer until liquid is absorbed (about 25 minutes). Transfer to a large bowl.
Cover and chill. Add turkey, mushrooms, spinach and onions.
Mix well. Blend wine, oil and seasonings.
Add to turkey mixture and mix gently. Chill.
Add tomatoes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana pie
directions: Place cans in saucepan and cover with water. Boil for 3 hours, making sure water covers cans throughout the boiling process. After 3 hours, set out of water until they become room temperature (when open, should be caramelized). In a 9-inch pie pan, line vanilla wafers. Layer 4 to 5 bananas on top of wafers and cover with Eagle Brand. Top with Cool Whip.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together cocoa and sugar; add margarine and milk.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Stir; drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: venison jerky
directions: Slice venison into thin strips.
(Partially frozen meat slices easier.)
Remove all fat.
Marinate meat in rest of ingredients in a large mixing bowl for 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator (may even be done overnight).
Lay strips of meat on wire racks, placing tinfoil under meat to catch drippings.
Oven should be set at lowest temperature possible (no higher than 150°).
Leaving the oven door open reduces heat even more.
Drying time varies on oven and thickness of meat, the norm being from 6 to 8 hours.
Meat should bend, "not break."

title: easy as 1-2-3 cheesecake
directions: Beat together well first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate 3 hours.

title: ham with potatoes
directions: Cut ham into 2-inch pieces and brown lightly on top burner. Place in triple kettle with other ingredients, potatoes (scrubbed but not peeled) on top.
Cook in Thermowell with 15 minutes of gas and 1 hour or longer of retained heat.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Put 1/2 of sugar mixture in bottom of dish.
Add apples. Cover with remainder of sugar; dot with butter.
Cover with pastry.
Put in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: she-crab soup
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and potatoes.
Cook over medium heat for about 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sherry before serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Heat fat in large skillet having tight fitting cover.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Add ground beef, breaking into small pieces.
Stir constantly until browned.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes (cut in pieces if whole) and spices.
Cayenne pepper may be hotter than desired, so starting with less than 1/8 teaspoon may be desirable.
Cover; simmer over low heat for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot with rolls or breadsticks. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: just good stuff
directions: You can melt this in microwave.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a large, oblong dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Heat a little before serving.

title: "best ever" meat sauce(beef, pork, chicken, all)
directions: Simmer ingredients for 15 minutes.
Use it for barbecue sauce for meat, or put in jar and keep in fridge like ketchup.

title: enchiladas
directions: Shred cheese and set aside.
Brown beef in skillet with onion and cilantro.
Add red pepper or chili pepper to season, if desired.
Drain beef and set aside.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; wash and drain.
Let cool.
Dice tomato, onion, pepper and cucumbers.
Add them to spaghetti; stir well. Add dressing; stir again.
Delicious.

title: cherry pudding
directions: In a double boiler, melt chocolate.
Add milk, sugar and salt, mixing well.
Add tapioca and cook until clear.
Stir in vanilla and let cool.

title: preacher's fried chicken
directions: Cut fryer into serving pieces. Steam chicken 20 minutes.
This can be done by placing chicken on sieve over boiling water. Cover and allow to steam.
Mix salt and pepper into pancake mix.

Beat egg and milk together. Dip each piece of chicken, while hot, into egg mixture, then roll in pancake mix until thoroughly coated. Heat fat and fry chicken in one layer until golden brown. Tag the 2 drumsticks "Preacher" and surprise the Pastor or guest clergy at homecoming or special church day.
Serve with hot orange marmalade.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into hot greased cast-iron skillet (8-inch).
If need large amount, double recipe and use skillet.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add other ingredients. Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cheese bread
directions: Combine butter and cheese; spread on both sides of each bread slice.
Sprinkle slices with poppy seed.
Place on baking sheet and toast in oven at 350° for 20 minutes, turning once.

title: deluxe leftover mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into oven proof dish. Bake at 350 degrees until top begins to brown.

title: date and nut cake(pudding)
directions: Pour soda mixture over dates.
Let cool.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg, salt and vanilla.
Next add dates and their liquid and nuts.
Sift flour with cream of tartar and beat this in last. Add cherries.
The batter will be quite thin.
Pour into greased glass baking dish; bake at 300° for an hour or until done.
Serve in sherbet glasses with a spoonful of whipped cream or any cake sauce.

title: ham casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in margarine.
Add cheese spread and milk; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Heat, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In bowl, toss cheese, spinach, pimento and onion with flour.
Add half and half, eggs, tarragon and salt, then crabmeat.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup(low-fat)
directions: The broccoli should be washed, trimmed, broken into small pieces and placed in a medium saucepan.
Add the remaining ingredients, except the milk, to the broccoli.
Cover, bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; blend at high speed until pureed.
Return mixture to saucepan.
Stir in evaporated milk; heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Yields four 1-cup servings with a fat content of 1 gram and 126 calories per serving.

title: homemade tandy kakes
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Take 1 cup milk and 2 tablespoons butter and heat until scalded.
Add to egg mixture.
Pour into greased 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Spread with peanut butter right out of oven.
Let cool.
Melt candy bars. Spread over cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla, then mix in zucchini.
Mix dry ingredients together, then combine with zucchini mixture. Use 2 greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Check after 1 hour.

title: 9-inch pat in the pan pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands until it's a soft dough.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie pan, being sure it is patted in evenly.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until it's a golden brown.

title: chocolate red beet cake
directions: Prepare the
beets
and blend in blender until chopped. Stir sugar,
oil,
baking
chocolate
and three eggs together, then blend in
beets.
Add
flour,
salt
and soda; beat well. Bake in moderate
350° oven in three layer pans.
Put together with Chocolate Powdered Sugar Frosting.

title: v-8 juice
directions: Combine tomatoes, garlic, onions, carrots, celery and green pepper in a large Dutch oven or soup kettle.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are soft. Cool.
Press mixture through a food mill or fine sleeve.
Return juice to Dutch oven; add sugar, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Pour hot juice into clean hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Add 2 tablespoons lemon juice to each jar.
Adjust caps.
Process for 40 minutes in a boiling water bath. Yield:
7 to 8 quarts.

title: good eating cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oranges and liquid and oil.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool. Remove from pan.
Frost with frosting.

title: mock chicken and dressing
directions: Combine all together. Spoon into 2-quart buttered casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. In a bowl, mix everything, except cake mix, pecans and butter. Pour into pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of mixture. Sprinkle pecans over top of mixture. Drizzle butter all over the mixture. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes; the edges will be brown. Good warm or cold with Cool Whip.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup tomato soup with the ground beef.
Add the rice, egg, onion, parsley and salt.
Shape into meatballs about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Brown in the shortening with the minced garlic.
Blend in the rest of the can of soup and the water. Cover.
Simmer about 40 minutes or until the rice is tender, stirring now and then.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Preheat broiler.
Meanwhile in medium sized bowl, mix sour cream, crumbled Blue cheese, parsley, mayonnaise, milk, lemon juice and salt to taste. Cover and refrigerate.

title: crock-pot simple stew
directions: Place vegetables in bottom of crock-pot.
Add meat.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat and vegetables.
Cook on low for 10 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Mix first 11 ingredients thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Add baking powder, eggs and milk.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Cut onions into thin slices.
Saute in margarine in skillet until tender.
Layer onions, cheese and cracker crumbs 1/2 at a time in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cow chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars, and eggs. Add karo and peanut butter. Next add soda. Mix in oats by 1 and 2 cups at a time. Bake at 325 for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple jalapeno salsa
directions: Process all ingredients briefly in food processor or mix as well as you can.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Serve as an appetizer with baked tortilla chips or as a relish. This is a pretty yellow and bright green salsa.
Yields 4 servings (1/4 cup each).
Has 40 calories, 0 fat grams.

title: blueberry buckwheat pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and sugar. In another bowl, combine the egg, buttermilk and sour cream. Combine all liquid ingredients and dry ingredients.
Stir with whisk.
Stir in butter until smooth.
Add blueberries.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute steak in 1/2 of the butter; set aside.
Drain most of the liquid.
Saute the onion and mushrooms in the rest of the butter.
Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add steak and small amount of liquid.
Simmer 5 more minutes.
Serve with toasted chow mein noodles.

title: stove top roast beef
directions: In a dutch oven, brown roast beef in oil. Sprinkle the rosemary on roast. Add the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil. Turn down the heat to a low simmer and cover. Cook for 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Check for liquid level and add water as needed. A very tender roast!!!

title: creamy green beans
directions: Place
all
ingredients in a microwave-safe 1 1/2 quart casserole.	Mix
well, cover and microwave on High power for 3 to 4 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: minnie bevill's orange cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line 18 muffin cups with paper bake cups. Set aside.
Cream the sugar and butter or margarine until light and fluffy. Add egg, orange peel and vanilla.
Mix well. Combine orange juice and milk.
Add orange juice mixture alternately with flour to creamed mixture. Mix just until combined after each addition.
Fill prepared muffin cups about 1/2 full. Bake 18 to 20 minutes. Cool and frost, if desired.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: carrot coins
directions: Slice carrots into coins.
Put each carrot piece on a toothpick and dip into peanut butter or dressing.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Let frozen dough thaw until pliable on lightly floured board. Roll dough out to a 10 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread dough with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Mix cinnamon, sugar, raisins and nuts. Set aside 2 tablespoons of mixture for later use.
Sprinkle mixture over dough.
Roll dough like a jelly roll and cut into 12 equal slices.
Place slices in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle with remaining cinnamon mixture.
Let rise until rolls have doubled in size.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and brush with remaining butter.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together. Combine yeast (dissolved in warm water) with buttermilk and oil. Mix liquids and dry ingredients together. Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Fill 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Do not let rise. Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: pastor's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate bars in a double boiler.
Slowly stir in milk and mix well.
Add	marshmallows,
a few at a time, until all are melted.
Remove
mixture from heat and cool thoroughly at room temperature.
When	cool
to
touch,
fold	in whipped cream
and pour
into	baked
pie
shell.
Chill
well before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fudge frosting(cooked)
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and boil 3 minutes, then add 1 cup chocolate chips and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat by hand until spreading consistency (about 15 minutes) and spread on cooled cake.

title: corn
directions: In large saucepan, cook onion and butter until clear.
Remove from heat, stir in flour, salt, paprika, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, stir constantly, until roux is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk gradually.
Heat to boiling.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Stir in egg and then corn.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: spitzaredu(spaghetti with potato sauce)
directions: In a saucepan, saute a little onion in a small amount of olive oil until translucent.
Add all the potato cubes and the can of tomato paste.
Keep stirring potatoes for about 20 minutes so they don't burn.
You can add a little water if it looks too thick. Stir until the potatoes are soft.
Fill the saucepan 3/4 full of water.
Add the remainder of ingredients (salt, pepper, basil, oregano and your meatballs) and let simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours. When completed, pour over spaghetti.

title: peggy aron's brunch quiche cups(24 cups)
directions: Blend flour, salt and butter, then add water.
Roll out dough and cut into 3-inch circles and fit into muffin pans.
Cover with damp cloth and refrigerate.

title: surprise cookies
directions: To one box of your favorite
cake
mix,
add one or two eggs, Cool Whip and mix well.
Form
into
teaspoon
balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup flour for firmer dough.
You may make your Cool Whip from
the
dry
package
according
to directions.
One or 1/2 cup nuts,
cherries
or
dates
may be added.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: caramels
directions: Stir together until butter is melted.
Cook over medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 240°.
Remove from stove and add nuts if desired.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Chill until set.
Cut
and wrap in waxed paper.

title: chicken `n' dumplings
directions: Heat first 7 ingredients to boil in large pot. Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Add potatoes, diced and peeled. After chicken has cooked 20 minutes, pull chicken from pot. Set aside to cool. Add vegetables except broccoli. Cut chicken into bite size pieces and return to pot. Mix Dumplings. Recipe follows. Add broccoli, cut in small pieces. Broccoli added last to maintain fresh look. Add Dumplings.

title: new sweet potato pie
directions: *Two cups mashed sweet potatoes equals 2 to 3 large potatoes or about 1 (17 ounce) can drained potatoes.

title: orange cheese salad
directions: Bring pineapple, sugar and water to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot mixture.
Cool in refrigerator until consistency of egg whites.
Add cheese and nuts.
Fold in dessert topping.
Pour into individual salad molds or one large mold.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onions and margarine until onions are clear.
Add soup and Ro-Tel and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add mushrooms, bell pepper and shrimp and cook until shrimp turns pink and curls.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve over rice.

title: country potato cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute vegetables in butter for 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Put mixture in blender and blend until smooth.
Return mixture to saucepan to heat. Stir in half and half. Add cheese. Heat until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: arizona baked beans(servings:  4)
directions: In a skillet, saute chopped onion with a teaspoon of butter. In a large baking pot, combine kidney beans, B & M baked beans, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and crumbled bacon. Combine and stir, adding sauteed onions; mix well.
Bake in a covered dish at 350° to 375° for 35 minutes or until piping hot.

title: shrimp bake
directions: Cook mushrooms in butter until tender.
Mix with shrimp, rice, vegetables and seasonings.
Place in greased 2-quart casserole. Pour 1/2 cup butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: diabetic berry pie(calories: 116 for 2 portions, 58 for 1 portion)
directions: Roll out very thin the pie crust and line a 5-inch pie plate. Bake.
Heat the berries over a moderate flame.
Place gelatin in a bowl and add a little water to soften.
Add the hot berries and saccharin or Sucaryl to taste, if desired.
Mix well and pour into baked pie crust.
When cool, place in refrigerator until time to serve.

title: candied apples
directions: Quarter the 5 apples into a large pot.
Rinse apples in the pot, draining the water off.
Add brown sugar and margarine.
Add cinnamon to taste.
Cover pot and cook on medium heat until steam starts to escape.
Turn heat to low or simmer and cook about 20 minutes.

title: chicken elizabeth
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate overnight.
Roll in stuffing mix (Pepperidge Farm).
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and 1/2 cup Crisco.
Pour half over chicken meat about 15 minutes from start and remaining mixture the last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: linguini with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat one tablespoon oil in heavy small skillet over medium-low heat.
Add garlic and stir three minutes; do not brown.
Transfer to non-aluminum bowl.
Mix in tomatoes and liquid, remaining 3 tablespoons oil, basil and vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper. Let stand six hours.
Just before serving, cook linguini in large amount of boiling, salted water until just tender, but still firm to bite.
Drain well.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add olive oil and toss well.
Add sauce and toss again.
Serves 6.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet 'n' sour dip
directions: Prepare mix according to package directions.
Heat sweet and sour sauce, stir in pineapple and green pepper.
Cool.
Good with egg rolls.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Heat oil in large iron skillet; add chicken tenders and cook until golden brown; remove from skillet.
Cut peppers, onions and tomatoes into strips and cook in same skillet (stir-fry).
Return chicken to skillet and stir in lime and lemon juice; mix well. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Warm tortillas in the microwave and fill.
Serve with guacamole and sour cream.

title: old-fashioned shortcake
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix cream and water.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Stir in the cream and water quickly.
Drop one heaping tablespoonful of dough in a flat circle on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart to allow for spreading.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: luxembourg salad
directions: Whisk the garlic, vinegar, lemon juice and mustard together in a mixing bowl.
Whisk in the herbs.
Gradually whisk in the oil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together.
Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Add vanilla and mix all together well.
Can add coconut or nuts also.
Spread into a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool in refrigerator and cut.
Can be frozen.
Good for large gathering.

title: chicken-pineapple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Reserve 1/4 cup pineapple juice for dressing.

title: yuck pie
directions: Cream
sugar and cream cheese together.
Mix Dream Whip up and fold
into cheese mixture.
Slice banana on bottom and pour cheese
filling in.
Pour blueberry pie filling on top of all.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in small amount of water until tender on top of stove. Drain; add sugar, eggs, mayo, salt and pepper. Pour into buttered dish. Cover with cheese, then cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: tri-pork chitterlings
directions: Boil 45 minutes to 1 hour in medium sized pot.
Cook meat and vegetables until tender.
Add water throughout the cooking process (meat should never stick).
Drain meat and vegetables, removing all liquid, except 1 1/2 cups.
Chop every ingredient finely in a wafer pan or iron skillet.
Place in the oven to bake.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into greased pan.
Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hawaiian ham
directions: Combine juice, broth and cornstarch in 3-quart casserole.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and microwave on High for 14 to 17 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate chip cookie ice cream sandwiches(prep time: 15 minutes; cook time: 15 minutes)
directions: You will need Dixie cups of ice cream.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Heat mixture of soup, chilies and seasonings.
Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, half of Doritos, half of chicken, half of cheese, half of onion and 1/2 of soup mixture.
Repeat layers. Save a little cheese and onion for top.
May be frozen and baked later.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all together and form meatballs.
Brown in skillet.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil brown sugar and Karo syrup in pan slowly.
Add rest of ingredients and boil until forms soft ball stage, 20 minutes. Pour over popped corn.

title: wimpy's rosy pickled eggs
directions: Use a 1/2 gallon container (glass).
Place beets, juice, vinegar and water in container.
Add ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs.
Refrigerate for 5 to 7 days.
God bless.

title: cajun shrimp fettucine
directions: Shell and devein shrimp. Dice bacon. Cook pasta as package directs. Drain and keep warm.
Cut shrimp in half lengthwise.
In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Stir in garlic and spices. Cook 1 minute. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until shrimp are cooked.
Just before serving, spoon sauce over hot fettucine. Makes 4 servings.
Serving size:
1 serving.
Preparation time: 30 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Layer in cake pan the peaches, dry cake mix, peaches and cake mix.
Put pats of butter on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over chicken.
Layer the cheese and stuffing mix on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream 3/4 cup of sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla until light.
Add milk, blending well.
Spoon flour (not sifted) into dry measuring cup.
Level off and pour onto waxed paper.
Add baking powder and salt to flour (not sifted).
Stir to blend.
Add blended dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Spread half of batter in well-greased 9-inch square pan.
Add blueberries over batter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Spread remaining batter over blueberries. Combine remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on batter.
Bake at 375°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange.
Add pineapple and other ingredients.
Chill.

title: cherry-pineapple crisp
directions: Pour layer of cherry pie filling on bottom of rectangle pan. Put layer of pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over this.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine flour with 2 teaspoons salt.
Coat cubes and brown in oil.
Add onion, garlic and marjoram.
Stir in V-8, bouillon and 2 1/2 cups of water.
Simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours.
Add celery and carrots and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Add mushrooms and heat through.

title: linden tree chicken salad
directions: Combine and cover.
Chill for one hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spiced christmas tea
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring water to boiling.
Add tea bags, anise and cinnamon stick.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags and cinnamon stick.
Stir in nectar, honey and lemon juice.
Heat through.
Pour tea mixture into four heatproof cups, floating a star anise on top of each. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pan and bake until done at 350°.

title: aunt maude's apple butter
directions: Measure cooked apple pulp.
For each quart, add the ingredients listed.
Bake in slow oven (325°), stirring occasionally, or simmer slowly.

title: old fashion egg custard
directions: Beat eggs and mix in sugar and flour.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into glass Pyrex dish or small serving dishes and bake at 350° until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Combine both soups, water and gravy mix.
Blend well.
Season roast with salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Put roast in roasting pan and add soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until roast is tender.

title: vegetable goulash
directions: Heat oil; saute onions and peppers until tender.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, mixed vegetables, paprika, salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to boil and cook over low heat until potatoes are tender (about 40 minutes).
Thicken with cornstarch mixed in water.
Serves 8.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first two ingredients.
Form into ball.
Roll ball in chopped nuts.
Wrap in Glad Wrap and refrigerate.
Can make ahead. Will keep up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken chunks, green chilies, onion, garlic powder, soups and broth.
Spread a layer of tortilla chips in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: mushroom soup pork chops
directions: Trim fat.
Beat with tenderizer.
Dip pork in egg and bread crumbs.
Fry until browned.
Drain on paper towel.
Add soup and water in a dish and place the pork chops in the dish; cover the soup.
This will make a nice gravy.
Bake at least 20 minutes or until the soup is as dark as you want it.

title: roast
directions: Rinse roast.
Place on foil.
Salt and pepper both sides. Wrap in foil.
Place wrapped roast in a deep dish or pan.
Add water to dish.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine the sausage with the eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt, bread and cheese.
Put in a well-greased pan.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together real well.
Make into 3 rolls in Reynolds Wrap (shiny side in).
Refrigerate for 24 hours, then bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Before baking, punch holes in bottom of rolls and bake on rack so grease will drain while rolls are baking.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomato sauce, with your hands. Shape into balls and place in a baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over the meat balls and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in double boiler over medium heat until melted.
Add light cream and sugar.
Gradually stirring after each time sugar is added.
Add condensed milk and let cook to thicken.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 375°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut pudding cake
directions: First Layer: Blend together butter, flour and 2/3 cup peanuts. Pat into bottom of a 13 x 9 pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: baked potato topping
directions: Mix all together and spoon over hot baked potato.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate if desired.

title: savory beef stew
directions: Brown beef in fat.
Add next 10 ingredients.
Simmer for two hours; stir occasionally.
Add carrots, onions and white potatoes. Continue cooking 20 to 30 minutes or until all vegetables are done. Remove meat and vegetables.
Thicken remaining liquid for gravy. (Wondra flour is good for this, as it does not cake.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with pineapple.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss lightly.

title: banana chocolate chip drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, water, shortening, bananas and about 1/2 the cake mix (dry) until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix, oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until tops are light brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet. Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: pastry for pies
directions: Add dry ingredients. Cut in shortening.
Add egg, water and vinegar; mix well.
Keep for one week in refrigerator.
Make 3 crusts with lattice strips.
Roll as needed per pie.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and rice together.
Mix golden mushroom soup and milk together and pour over first mixture.
Melt butter and pour over that mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: connie's chicken salad
