directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers or bread.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water for 10 minutes.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread a small amount of the sauce. Layer half the noodles in the dish.
Top with half the zucchini slices, half the sauce and half the Mozzarella cheese in layers. Repeat layers of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: the best chocolate cake ever!
directions: Cream together cream cheese, 1/2 C. butter and vanilla.
Add powdered sugar and 1/3 C. milk.
Add cocoa and Crisco.
Mix well. Remove 2 C. of mixture to use for frosting.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix sugar, flour and rind.
Beat in eggs
at a time.
Stir in lemon juice and melted butter, adding a
bit
at a time and beating well after each addition. Pour filling
into pie shell and bake about 1 hour until puffy and golden
(filling
will
seem
unset or very soft).	As pie cools to room temperature the filling will settle and thicken. Serve at room temperature.
Makes 1 pie.

title: tucson hash
directions: Saute onion until soft in oil. Stir in chili powder and beef; saute 2 minutes. Add celery and saute 3 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients except chips. Spoon into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with chips and bake 10 minutes longer. Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Dump in undrained pineapple, swirling it around to fill corners.
Dump in pie filling and push it around until layers of fruit are quite even.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the fruit to cover it all.
Melt butter and dribble over top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° until browned, about 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: layered hot taco dip
directions: Layer in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with taco chips.

title: roast wild duck
directions: Rinse duck and pat dry.
Sprinkle inside and outside of duck with salt and pepper.
Stuff inside cavity with carrots and celery.
Place in pan and top with bacon.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Baste often.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt almond bark in 200° oven on foil lined cookie sheet until smooth.
Pour on dry ingredients. Fold until covered with bark.
Spread out.
Cool.
Break into pieces.

title: cabbage dinner
directions: Brown meat; add onion and green pepper, cook until done. Drain.
Put meat mixture into a large pot and add seasonings, cabbage, tomatoes, tomato sauce, rice, egg, oil and water.
Stir a little and cook 1 hour on low.
Stir occasionally. Serve with cornbread muffins.

title: cream cheese
directions: Combine heavy cream with buttermilk, then suspend mixture in a piece of cloth (tight woven) over a bowl for 24 hours or until cream thickens.
(The longer you leave it suspended, the drier it will be.)
Season with salt to taste.

title: universal pickle
directions: Put all ingredients in stone jar, 4 or 5 gallon kind.
Put any kind of vegetable and stir thoroughly for 9 days, then they are ready to eat.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg yolks and whites separately.

title: duck gumbo
directions: Mix all together in a large pot and simmer approximately 2 hours, stirring often.
Serve over rice.

title: old fashioned gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add molasses; beat well.
Mix in flour alternately with hot water; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Butter baking dish.
Combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, oil and milk.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Top with apples.
Cover apples with remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until apples and batter are baked.

title: bul-ko-kee(korean marinated beef)
directions: Trim fat from beef; cut diagonally across into 1/8-inch slices.
(For ease in cutting, partially freeze beef, about 1 1/2 hours.)
Mix remaining ingredients; stir in beef until well coated.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Drain garden peas.
Add 1 small chopped onion and 3 boiled eggs, chopped. Add salt and pepper.
Mix with mayonnaise.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease baking dish and fill with apples, water and cinnamon. Mix sugar, flour and butter.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan and add sour cream, soup and onions with cooked potatoes in crock-pot on low heat.
Heat for at least 1 hour.

title: pineapple ginger chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in casserole. Gradually mix flour with barbecue sauce until well blended.
Add pineapple syrup, honey, ginger and Tabasco sauce to barbecue sauce.
Pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover. Continue baking until chicken is done. Baste every once in awhile with sauce. Serve over rice.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, green peppers and celery in oil until tender. Add tomato sauce, bay leaf and hot sauce.
Let simmer about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook about 10 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over rice.

title: amish peanut butter cream cheese pie
directions: In a small bowl, beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk, beat until smooth and creamy.

title: frothy lime sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet. Drink and enjoy.
Add more ginger ale as needed.
This is a quick and easy recipe for punch that anyone can follow.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Sift the dry ingredients into the top of a double boiler; add the water and egg yolks.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook mixture over hot water in the double boiler, stirring frequently, until thick, about 15 minutes.
Add the lemon juice and grated rind; mix well. Cool.
Pour into pie shell and top with your favorite meringue made with the two egg whites.
Brown in oven.
Cool and serve.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Boil three cups water.
Add three slices bacon, salt and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes, then add cut up cabbage and cut up pepper.
Cook for 20 minutes, then serve hot.

title: chocolate cake pudding(to sara with lots of love)
directions: Sift 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt into 9-inch square pan.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Spread evenly in pan.
Combine next 3 ingredients; sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over top.
Bake pudding at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or ice cream (optional).

title: irish soda bread(makes 2 round loaves)
directions: You will need two 8-inch cake or pie pans, greased or Teflon. If glass pans are used, reduce heat by 25°.

title: aunt esther's caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Bring all ingredients except popped corn and soda to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and carefully add soda. Pour over the popped corn. Place in oven for 1 hour. Stir every 10 to 15 minutes. Yum!

title: easy overnight tuna casserole
directions: Lightly coat 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray. In casserole dish, combine pasta, vegetables, soup, cheese, milk and tuna.
Refrigerate, covered, 12 hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine margarine and crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: black bean lasagna(vegetarian)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13x9 inch pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, mash the beans slightly.
Stir in the tomatoes, onions, green peppers, salsa, chili powder and cumin.
Mix well. In a separate bowl, combine the ricotta, garlic powder, and egg.

title: onion dip
directions: Mix and serve dip in cleaned out bell pepper, acorn squash cut in half and cleaned.
Different vegetables make attractive serving dishes.

title: jam cake
directions: Have eggs and butter at room temperature; cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour three times; add soda and cinnamon and sift again.
Add about half of the flour mixture to the creamed sugar, butter and egg mixture.
Beat well.
Add buttermilk and jam, mixing well.
Mix raisins and nuts with remaining flour,
being sure to coat well.
Add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until it holds a stiff peak.
Then fold in batter with a spatula.
Grease 3 round pans and cut wax paper to fit.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Cool completely before icing.

title: low cholesterol cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients; beat vigorously 30 seconds.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray (round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches or square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or 10-inch ovenproof skillet).
Bake until golden brown, 25 minutes.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt oleo in 2-quart pot. Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat.
Sift in flour.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Pat in Pyrex pan, oiled and floured.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add broth until you have a smooth consistency.
Do not cook.
Serve immediately.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook
8	minutes on full power, stirring well after 4 minutes.
Stir
in	butter	and
vanilla
and
cook
2 minutes longer
on	full
power.
Add
baking soda and quickly stir until light and foamy.

title: veal guiseppe
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Dip veal in flour; place in oil when hot.
Saute until veal is white.
Drain oil and add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and let simmer until sauce is thickened and serve.
Yield:
1 serving.

title: shrimp plate
directions: Mix the first four ingredients and spread on plate.
Pour 1/2 bottle Heinz chili sauce over cheese mixture.
Place shrimp on top and garnish with parsley flakes.
Prepare 24 hours prior to serving.

title: macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.

Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl. Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended. Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes or until edges of cookies are slightly brown.
Remove immediately from sheet. Cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple (with juice) to just below boiling point.
Add Jell-O; stir to dissolve.
Cool to room temperature.
Blend in buttermilk and refrigerate until partly set.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until served.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.

Cook onion in hot oil just until tender. Combine egg and milk. Add to biscuit mix. Stir until moistened. Add onion, half of cheese and parsley. Spread dough in greased round cake pan. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and parsley. Drizzle butter over this. Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes about 6 servings.

title: "easy" chicken pot pie
directions: Thaw pie crust (follow crust directions for 2 crust pie). Boil chicken breast in water with desired seasoning.
Cool chicken; chop up.
Mix chicken, vegetables, soup, milk and seasonings.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes until golden brown.
Great with a salad!

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple, saving liquid.
Add enough hot water to liquid to make 2 1/2 cups of liquid.
Heat and dissolve jello in
the juice.
Add frozen orange juice, undiluted, and when almost set, add fruit, saving a few orange segments.
Pour into a ring Jell-O mold or a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: savory beef and vegetable stew
directions: In hot oil in Dutch oven, brown beef cubes well on all sides. Remove and set aside.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery to Dutch oven.
Saute until tender, about 8 minutes.
Return beef to pan.
Add parsley, garlic, tomato sauce, wine, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, thyme, bay leaf and 2 cups of water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: egg bake
directions: Oil 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine croutons and cheese. Place in bottom of dish.
Lightly beat eggs together with milk, salt, onion powder, mustard and pepper.
Pour over crouton cheese mixture.
Sprinkle bacon over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 50 minutes or until set.
Serves 12.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 buttered casserole dish.

title: holiday gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in one cup boiling water.
With a whisk, thoroughly blend in yogurt.
Stir in pineapple, including juice. Mix in cherries and nuts and pour into a gelatin mold.
Chill until set. Makes 8 to 10 half-cup servings.

title: marinated cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Place over medium heat and bring to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Set aside to cool.
Shred cabbage, onion and carrots.
Pour liquid over vegetable mixture.
Add mayonnaise and stir well.

title: irish cream and coffee pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Dissolve coffee into boiling water; stir in liqueur.
Add flour to butter mixture alternately with coffee mixture, beginning and ending with flour.

title: jill's burlas
directions: Line pan with wax or aluminum paper.
Melt margarine; add rest of the ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Crumble the corn bread and biscuits or put in a blender.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Add enough broth for it to be standing on the top.
Cook in a 400° oven until done, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: tortilla squares(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Line bottom of jelly roll pan with one layer of tortillas. Spread 1/2 of soup and half of chilies and ample amount of cheese over this.
Repeat process, making another complete layer.
Bake in 350° oven until heated and cheese is melted.
Cut into diamonds or squares and serve warm or cold.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Mix in order given; bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together, except grated cheese.
Do not drain the whole kernel corn.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry nut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set until you mix pastry.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes. Good Christmas pie.

title: pralines
directions: Mix ingredients and place in pot; let boil until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Takes about 5 minutes.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: ten bean soup
directions: Soak mixed beans overnight and drain.
Add 2 quarts water, ham, chopped onion, garlic and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Boil carrots until half done.
Drain, then pour cold water over them.
Pour into serving bowl.

title: ken's kookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour and mix well.
Add nuts
and chips or bits (or add all three).
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cut up peaches and peel them.
Mix up all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° until top rises and starts to brown.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix with fork butter, sugar and flour in the 9-inch square pan.
Add baking powder.
Stir in milk.
Drop pie filling on top of batter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla, sour cream and zucchini.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine and heat just to the boiling point, but do not boil. Let stand for at least one hour.
Serve with cinnamon and cookies.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onions, carrots and squash until tender.
Mash squash in strainer.
Add soup, cheese, sour cream, butter and 1 1/2 cups stuffing.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put all ingredients together and put in greased baking dish.
Top with 1 cup stuffing.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: bridal shower punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, then add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up just before serving.
Garnish punch with orange or lemon slices.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except almonds, and form into a large ball. Cover with almonds and place in refrigerator over night. Serve with Ritz or Townhouse crackers.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool a few minutes before serving with crackers.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on sheet of aluminum foil.
Flatten slightly with hand.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 100 to 120 cookies. Children love to help.

title: easy fresh baked salmon
directions: Select 1 to 2 pound salmon filet(s).
Spray cooking oil, etc., on bottom of casserole dish.
Wash off and drain salmon filet and place in long, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and Bay seasoning.
Dot with margarine and spread mayonnaise over top surface of fish.
Then squirt "Real" lemon juice over fish and sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake in oven preheated at 350° to 375° for 50 minutes.
Melts in your mouth!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt in large glass bowl. Microwave on High for 7 to 9 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla and microwave on High for 2 to 3 more minutes.
Stir in baking soda and pour immediately on a buttered cookie sheet.
Allow to cool completely and break into pieces.

title: crystal salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool. Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until solid.

title: aunt avis' candy
directions: Heat 1 cup sugar and milk while melting the other 1 cup sugar in heavy pan.
Combine the two mixtures.
Add soda (be careful, this boils up quickly).
Add pecans immediately.
Boil slowly to 237° on candy thermometer.
Beat by hand and add butter.
Pour out to harden.
Break into pieces.
Enjoy!

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cool.
Add seasonings and spaghetti sauce. Put on bun half.
Top with thin slice of cheese.
Bake 12 minutes at 425°.

title: hot peppers in sweet juice
directions: Clean tops and seeds from banana peppers or other hot peppers. Cut into chunks.
Put in slowly boiling liquid.
Boil 5 to 7 minutes; put in jars and seal.
Make more juice as needed according to measurement given.
If you place them in jars tight, you will use less juice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls (walnut size).
Cook at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: aunt ruth's mystery rolls
directions: Add shortening, salt, sugar and crumbled yeast to water and stir until shortening is melted. Stir in sifted flour; cover and set aside in a warm place, free from drafts, to rise. When doubled in bulk, add egg. Knead lightly and let rise again until doubled in bulk. Roll out 1/2-inch thick on a well floured board and cut with biscuit cutter 2-inches in diameter (or just pinch off the desired amount). Place in greased cups; top with butter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: gumbo pork chops(the working family)
directions: Brown and season pork chops in a skillet.
Pour soup over pork chops (do not add water) and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour. Cook rice according to package directions.
Serve pork chops and gravy over rice.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soften	bread
pieces
in
the	milk.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place
in loaf pan.
Spread 3 tablespoons catsup over the top before baking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: party punch
directions: Combine juices with 1/2 pineapple juice can water in large container.
Mix until frozen juices are thawed.
Add sherbet and ginger ale.
Chill until serving time.
Yields 50 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes.
Add salsa.
Microwave for 5 minutes until melted.
Brown beef and mix with cheese and salsa mixture. Place in serving dish with nacho or tortilla chips on side.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Cream together egg yolks and sugar; add butter and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick, about 12 minutes.
Take off heat and add 1 1/3 cups coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Beat until thick enough to spread.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.
Good on German Chocolate Cake.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and boil approximately 15 minutes. Drain and add remaining ingredients and gently stir (potatoes will become mushy if stirred too hard).
Serve hot or cold.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Line casserole dish with Tater Tots.
Mix ground beef, vegetables, onions and remaining Tater Tots; pour soups over this and top with cheese.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, 1 cup of grated cheese, sour cream and the green onions.
Add to spuds and oleo; stir gently.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with a mixture of 1 cup Cheddar cheese and cornflake crumbs.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: chocolate lush 3 layer pie
directions: Flour and Butter Crust:
Use the flour, butter and nuts.

title: sweet celery seed dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together slowly until well blended.
Good on cabbage slaw or fruit salad.

title: baked donuts
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and egg until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by tablespoon into well-greased small size muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Shake in bag with confectioners sugar or sugar or a mixture of cinnamon and sugar until coated.

title: whacky cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add the cut up chicken and shake to coat.
Combine all other ingredients in small saucepan to make a sauce.
Tear aluminum foil in squares large enough for each individual piece of chicken.
Place one piece chicken on each piece of foil.
Spoon sauce over chicken in foil.
Fold foil and seal.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: flour totilla roll-ups
directions: Mix dressing and cream cheese together. Spread on torillas. Sprinkle broccoli, bacon bits, nuts and cheese.
Roll up and slice into 1 in. slices. Place cut side down in pan and refrigerate 1 hr. before serving.
Note; make sure that the dressing is all the way to the edge so when you roll them up it sticks together.

title: grilled chicken and tortellini salad
directions: Place chicken in a plastic bag, set into a shallow dish.
Pour Italian dressing over chicken.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning bag several times to distribute marinade. Drain chicken.
Grill, uncovered, over coals for 10 to 12 minutes or until tender.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook fresh tortellini in 3 1/2 quarts boiling salted water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender but still firm (or cook frozen tortellini per package directions).
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain well.
In medium bowl combine mayonnaise, eggs, red pepper, tomatoes, salt, pepper, chicken and tortellini; mix well.
Add additional mayonnaise, if necessary, to reach desired consistency. Makes 6 servings.
Enjoy!!

title: chicken mushroom fettuccine
directions: Saut mushrooms, onion and garlic in oil.
Stir in chicken, salt, pepper and basil.
Saut until chicken is fully cooked.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over pasta.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken, boiled eggs and vegetables.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Mix soup and hot broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Add melted oleo.
Pour this over the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: "hello dolly" cookies
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour over it the graham crackers (do not stir).
Spread coconut over crumbs (do not stir).
Sprinkle chocolate chips over, do not stir.
Spread nuts over this (do not stir).
Pour milk over this (do not stir). Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar at room temperature.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add flour and whipping cream.
Cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: needhams
directions: Melt margarine; add potatoes, coconut, etc.
Mix well.
Pack in buttered cookie sheet; put in refrigerator.
Let harden overnight.
Cut into small pieces.

title: shortbread
directions: Sift flour and confectioners sugar into bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips. Spread in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes or until light brown.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Cut into bars.
Yields 27 bars.

title: old timey pickles
directions: Wash small cucumbers.
Bring vinegar, water, sugar, salt and spices to rolling boil.
Drop cucumbers in boiling mixture until they change color.
Pack in jars and cover with boiling mixture. Seal.

title: garden zucchini bread
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together.
Add flour, zucchini, sugar and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make the cake (follow the directions on box) in a sheet cake pan.
Let it cool.
Poke holes all over top of cake (pencil point size).
Strain the juice from the pineapple.
Pour the juice over the cake. It should soak into cake.

Now take the pineapple and pudding mix and put into blender. Mix real good so that the pineapple is fine. Fold the Cool Whip into the pineapple mix. Spread over your cake. Keep in the refrigerator until you are ready to eat.
Enjoy.

title: asparagus goldenrod
directions: To prepare asparagus:
Snap tough ends off.
Wash in warm water.
Boil or steam 10 minutes.

title: south of the border salad
directions: Cook pork or ground beef, onions and garlic until meat is browned and onions tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, chili peppers, flour and chili powder.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
In salad bowl, mix lettuce, beans and olives.
Toss.
Top with meat mixture.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Top with cherry tomato halves and green pepper strips.
Peel and slice avocado.
Arrange slices on top of salad.

title: uncle ben's wild rice dressing
directions: Saute the first five ingredients.
Put in casserole with mushroom soup and mushroom pieces.
Bake 1/2 to 1 hour at 350°.

title: jean harshaw's white bread
directions: Mix hot water, butter and sugar.
Cool	until lukewarm, add yeast.
Add 3 cups flour, beat well and
add 3 cups flour; knead well.
May have to add more flour.	Don't
add
too much as
to make
dough
stiff.
Cover and let	rise
until
dough doubles. Punch down and let rise again.
Shape
in loaves and place in well-greased pans.	Let rise to double in size.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Stir in strawberries and juice.
Add pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Stir until well mixed. Pour half of mixture into a one-quart mold and chill for 20 minutes.
Spread sour cream over chilled mixture and top with remaining jello mixture.
Chill several hours until firm.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in microwave safe bowl, cook on high for 5 minutes. Add peanuts and cook on high for an additional 3 minutes. Add the last 3 ingredients and microwave on high 1 minute. Spread candy in a buttered pan and let cook. Break into pieces to serve.

title: cola bbq sauce
directions: Combine Coke and remaining ingredients (except honey) in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, simmer 6 minutes. Stir in honey, cool. Serve with grilled or roasted chicken.

title: home-made mayonnaise
directions: Put egg, salt, mustard, juice, and 1/4 c. oil into blender. Cover, turn on low speed.
Remove cap and add remaining oil in steady stream. Use only as much oil as is absorbed in mayonnaise.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground beef together.
Mix in the beans with chili.
Turn mixture
into
casserole
and
cover
with a layer of your favorite
cheese.
Then
cover
cheese with corn chips.
Bake uncovered in moderate oven, about 350°, for about 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Steam broccoli till partially cooked (3 min.); cool and press dry.
Beat eggs with milk till blended thoroughly.
Mix flour, baking power and salt; stir into egg and milk.
Fold in broccoli, cheese, onion and butter.
Spoon into a greased 13x9-inch pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven about 35 minutes or till lightly brown. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: tangy cheese spread
directions: In a small mixing bowl, beat together cottage, Cheddar and Blue cheeses at highest speed of mixer until fairly smooth.
Beat in onions, horseradish and mustard. Cover and chill to blend flavors. Allow to come to room temperature before serving.
Serve with apple slices or crackers.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line small muffin pans with paper baking cups and place a vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
Fill cups 2/3 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until set at 375°.
Top each with about 1 tablespoon cherry pie filling. Chill.
Place in refrigerator until serving time.
Serves 24.
Use baking cups that vanilla wafer will fit in.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Mix well the first three ingredients.
Place chicken breasts in baking dish and pour mixture over.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: blueberry cheese pie(serves 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (180°C).
Soften cream cheese.
Beat the eggs.
Beat in the cream cheese.
Add the cream.
Fold in lemon rind and 2 cups of blueberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in oven 30 minutes.
Remove.
In saucepan, add the 2 cups of blueberries, lemon juice, apple juice, sugar and cornstarch. Blend thoroughly.
Heat over low heat until mixture thickens. Pour on top of pie.
Chill 3 hours.

title: frosty cranberry swirl
directions: Leftover cranberry sauce makes a colorful, kid-pleasing dessert.
In a blender container, combine cranberry sauce with vanilla ice cream.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Layer this cranberry mixture with additional softened vanilla ice cream, then cover and freeze until firm.
Pack this frozen dessert into paper cups or yogurt containers and use them as snacks.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store.
Put 2 to 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Serve hot.

title: onion cheese supper bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Saute onions in butter until tender and light brown.
Combine egg and milk.
Add Bisquick and stir until blended.
Add onion and 1 cup of the cheese.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice; beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Stir in pecans and fruit. Pour into pie crusts and refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 2 nine-inch pies.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place deboned chicken into a prepared casserole dish.
Top the chicken with a mixture of the broth and chicken soup.
Add sliced, hard-boiled eggs over the soup mix.

title: overnight egg casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place croutons on bottom. Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Brown sausages and cut into small pieces. Drain.
Place over cheese layer.
Beat eggs; combine with milk and seasonings.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, dilute soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Pour over first mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese on top and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or less.

title: mushroom-potato chowder
directions: Melt butter in a large Dutch oven.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring frequently, until tender. Stir in potato, chicken broth and thyme.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of milk, salt and pepper.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup milk and flour, stirring until smooth.
Stir into chowder and simmer, uncovered, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened.
Yields 1 1/2 quarts.
Excellent soup.

title: fruit and nut tropical slaw
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons syrup.
Cut up pineapple; set aside.
Combine the reserved syrup and lemon juice. Coat banana slices with 1 tablespoon of juice mixture.
Set remaining juice aside.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, banana, cabbage, celery, oranges, nuts and raisins.
Blend the reserved juice mixture with the yogurt and salt.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on crackers or bread.

title: apple pudding
directions: Add sugar to apples and let stand 30 minutes, then add soda, cinnamon and eggs.
Mix well.
Blend in flour; stir in nuts, raisins and salt.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 1 1/2-quart oblong dish.
Serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: black magic cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs, coffee, milk, oil and vanilla; beat at medium speed 2 minutes (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes for layers.

title: french roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Crumble cheese and add to dressing.
Refrigerate.

title: inexpensive bread
directions: Start with 2 cups of flour, beat really well into other ingredients.
Keep adding flour until dough is still sticky. Knead on floured surface until punchy.
Let rise in a greased bowl until twice its size.
Place in greased loaf pans and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cool on racks, butter and cover with paper towel.

title: bourbon pecan pork roast
directions: Work time equals 15 minutes.
Total time equals 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: judy's linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Cook linguine following package directions.
Drain; keep warm. Drain clams, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
In a microwave-safe 1-quart dish, micro-cook onion, garlic and margarine, covered, on 100% power (High) 1 to 2 minutes or until onions are tender.
Stir in flour and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring after each minute.
Add clams, reserved juice, olives and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 1 to 2 minutes more or until the mixture is heated through.
Toss with linguine until coated.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: frozen cranberry velvet pie
directions: Combine crumbs and melted butter; press firmly into bottom of buttered 9-inch pie plate. Chill until firm. Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Combine whipping cream, sugar, and vanilla. Whip until thickened but not stiff. Gradually add to whipped cream cheese. Beat until smooth and creamy. Fold cranberry sauce into whipped mixture. Spoon into chilled crust. Freeze firm. Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving. Top with additional whipped cream.

title: jiffy cranberry refrigerator cake
directions: Fold stiffly beaten egg whites into sauce.
Arrange alternate layers of sauce and sliced cake, ending with cake on top.
Place weight on top and chill. Serve with whipped cream.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jellos in hot water.
Add cold water.
Slightly congeal.
Add bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.

title: old fashioned pot roast
directions: In heavy pan or Dutch oven brown roast in 2 tablespoons oil. Add soup and water.
Cover tightly and simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until tender, turn occasionally.
Potatoes, carrots, celery or onion may be added and simmer another 20 to 30 minutes.
Thicken gravy if desired.

title: meringue cookies(these are also known as suspiros, spanish for "sighs".)
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually while continuing to beat until sugar is incorporated and dissolved.
Add lemon juice, then fold in almonds.
Line a baking sheet with foil. Drop meringue mixture by teaspoonfuls onto foil.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 36 to 48 cookies.

title: chicken divan
directions: In 2-quart baking dish or 9-inch pie plate, arrange broccoli and chicken.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and form into small balls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
These can be frozen and reheated as needed.

title: marinated black-eyed pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; toss to mix. Refrigerate overnight.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: apple coleslaw
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, celery seed, sugar, salt and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Stir well.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil and mix.
Stir in zucchini.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Bake in two loaf pans at 325° for one hour.

title: black olive dip
directions: Chop olives, onions and tomatoes.
Mix with picante sauce. Chill.
Longer dip chills, the hotter it gets.
Serve with corn chips.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Stir in ground beef. Roll out mixture to about 1/2-inch thick. Arrange ham slices on hamburger mixture. Add cheese and roll up.
Pinch ends closed.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: ashley's scrambled eggs
directions: Grease frying pan.
In a small bowl, mix eggs, milk, garlic salt and salt.
Pour in pan on stove.
Turn heat on low for 5 to 6 minutes until done.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla. Add Cool Whip and hand mix until well mixed. Cut pound cake into small cubes and stir into mixture until well coated. Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan evenly. Pour blueberry pie filling evenly over top and spread with back of spoon. Refrigerate over night.

title: jeff davis pie
directions: Beat egg whites until
foamy.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition until sugar is blended. Continue beating until stiff peaks
form.
Bake in a slow oven until lightly browned.

title: microwave fudge(servings:  20)
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk with butter in glass bowl for 2 minutes on High.
Remove from microwave.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Freeze for 20 minutes or refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain liquid from pears into saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Remove from heat and cool until syrupy. Meanwhile, puree pears in blender.

title: pumpkin bread(from 1975 edition)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add wet and mix.
Put in three 4 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Saute bacon and drain.
Add butter to pan and saute peppers, onions, ham and mushrooms.
Add flour, salt and pepper to taste. While mixing, gradually add 1 quart of milk until thickened and smooth.
Set aside.
Scramble eggs, milk (evaporated) and cheese; salt to taste.
Alternate layers:
2 of sauce, 2 of eggs.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
This can be made a day ahead and cooked when needed. Delicious for a brunch.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar; beat well.
Add vanilla and almond and mix, then add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar, a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold egg yolk mixture into egg whites.
Add flour gradually and gently fold after each addition. Pour batter into ungreased tube pan. Cut batter with spatula in pan to prevent holes in cake.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes. Invert pan to cool before removing cake.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch Bundt cake pan with 2 tablespoons

butter. Press almonds in the sides and bottom of pan; set aside. Melt remaining butter. In a large mixing bowl, beat the cake mix, eggnog, eggs, rum extract, nutmeg and melted butter on low speed for 30 seconds until moistened. Then beat on medium speed for 2 minutes or until smooth. Pour into prepared pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until pick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Mix gelatin, mayonnaise and cream cheese until light in color. Add hot water and juice from fruit cocktail and allow to cool. When gelatin mixture begins to set, add remaining ingredients. Chill.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: cauliflower with vegetables
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
When smooth, add Cheddar cheese.
When cheese is melted, pour sauce over cooked vegetables.

title: nevelle's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa.
Add to mixture, alternating with milk. Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: gingered peach crisp
directions: Combine crushed gingersnaps and next 2 ingredients.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles corn meal.
Arrange peaches in an 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle gingersnap mixture over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with vanilla ice milk.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sherry pound cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan heavily.
Sprinkle with sugar and sliced almonds.
Mix all ingredients and pour in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Let stand for 10 minutes, then put on plate.

title: fruit punch(serves 75 to 100)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O, Kool-Aid and sugar and combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Keep frozen until about one hour before using and thaw to a slush.
Add ginger ale (as desired).
(You may use all sweetened juices.)

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix and fold together. Pour in graham crust.
Chill and serve.

title: nut logs
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a large bowl. Add butter, milk, brown sugar and egg.
Mix until well blended. Stir in vanilla and nutmeats.
Use about 1 teaspoon of dough to form small log.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until browned.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together in large bowl.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Arrange by teaspoonfuls on unbuttered cookie sheet and bake until edges are brown, about 12 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well with hands, rolling into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
To freeze, put balls onto your cookie sheet and place them in the freezer.
When the balls are frozen, you can put them into plastic bags without them sticking together, and return to the freezer.

title: carrot patties
directions: Scrape the carrots, cut into small pieces and cover with hot water.
Add salt to taste and sugar.
Cook until done, drain and mash.
Add self-rising flour.
Stir sifted flour into the mashed carrots.
Make round flat patties of the carrots.
Fry in hot cooking oil.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture is bubbly. Remove from heat.
Add cream of mushroom soup and mix well.
In a greased casserole dish place a layer of potatoes.
Top with sauce, and then a layer of onions.
Sprinkle lightly with bacon bits.
Top with a layer of American cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: zucchini finger-tip food
directions: Stir and mix all ingredients together.
Pour in an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake 30 or 40 minutes.
Let it get slightly browned. Serve warm or cold.

title: raspberry jam "thumbprint cookies"
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Separate yolk from egg white (discard white).
Add yolk, vanilla, salt and flour.
Mix well. Shape into balls.
Roll in pecans.

title: skillet scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter or fat in pan over low heat.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook and stir until most of the fat is absorbed (3 to 4 minutes).
Add water; stir in milk.

title: sara's hot chicken dip
directions: *It is best to use fresh, cooked chicken breast when possible.

title: refrigerator cucumber slices
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions. In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Pour over cukes and onions mixture; mix well. Cover and chill overnight. May be refrigerated up to 2 weeks.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour.
Gradually stir in water, then broccoli, bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes.
Add cheese and cream.
Cook and stir (do not boil).
Garnish as desired.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour with spices and salt.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in molasses and hot water.
Add flour mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cheese cake(crock-pot cooking)
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into greased crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours or on high setting for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Yields 4 to 6 servings (about 2 quarts).
Double recipe for 5-quart crock-pot.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Melt chips and butter.
Add sugar and milk, blending well. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil and cook for 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Serve sauce warm.
Yields 2 3/4 cups.
Serve over ice cream, cake or pudding.

title: icebox lemon pies
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and condensed milk; pour into pie shells.
Freeze pies; serve frozen.

title: lemon lush
directions: Combine the pecans, flour and butter.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes; let cool.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix juice and 1 can water.
Dissolve Sweet 'N Low in 1 cup warm water.
Add to juice.
Add remaining fruit.
Freeze.
Let thaw a little before serving.
Can be frozen in 8 ounce butter tubs for individual servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix well and put into a well buttered 9x13-inch pan.
Sprinkle YELLOW CAKE MIX (dry) over the top and pat down.
Drizzle 1 1/2 cube MELTED BUTTER on top.
Bake at 325° one hour.

title: tomato-basil salad
directions: Cut the garlic and rub a shallow serving dish with it.
Slice the olives, tomatoes and mushrooms and arrange in the dish.
Mix the oil and vinegar and pour over the vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon bits in bowl.
Add sugar and vinegar to salad dressing.
Mix well.
Pour over salad, tossing to coat vegetables.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: homemade buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in water.
Heat milk and oil to warm. Combine yeast mixture with milk mixture and rest of ingredients. Mix well and let stand for ten minutes.
Make into rolls and let rise 30 minutes.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: mom's jam cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs, molasses, juice and jam. Sift all dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients alternately with bourbon. Stir in cherries, figs, dates and raisins. Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and lined cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Brown onion in butter in a large saucepan or skillet.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add milk and cook, stirring until smooth.
Add cheese.
Stir until smooth and melted.
Add ham and macaroni.

title: apple cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 cake pan with Pam. Beat the eggs and sugar for 5 minutes. Add the oil, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt. Stir in apples and walnuts. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bubble trouble
directions: Place ice in glass.
Add the club soda and then the fruit juice.
Watch for bubbles!
Serves 1. Use pineapple, cherry, apple, cranberry, grape, orange juices.

title: slow cooked b.b.q. pork or beef
directions: Brown meat on all sides. Put B.B.Q. sauce into slow cooker. Set on high and add 2 bottles of water, stir, then add meat to mixture. Sprinkle onion over and around sides of meat and top with the onion soup mix. When mixture begins to boil, turn down to low and cook for 10 hours. This roast will fall to pieces and melt in your mouth.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Mix well and freeze in molds or small paper cups.

title: washboard cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and egg.
Stir together baking soda and water.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Shape into walnut-sized balls.

title: chicken saronno
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, garlic powder and curry in a bowl.
Heat butter in a large skillet.
Dip chicken strips in flour mixture and brown in skillet.
Brown both sides of chicken, then add Amaretto and lemon.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Mix chicken broth and cornstarch together.
Stir into mixture in the skillet.
Stir until sauce thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix quick oats with hot water and set aside and let stand. Mix sugars, eggs, flour, shortening, soda and spices.
Add oatmeal.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown the meat, half at a time in the shortening or oil.
Drain oil; return all the meat to the pan. Add 4 cups water, onions, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/4 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in corn, beans and peas.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: hurry pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into two 9-inch graham cracker crusts.
Chill for 30 minutes.
This is much like a cheese cake.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine egg, bread crumbs, chopped onion, milk and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Shape into 24 one-ounce balls.
Brown meatballs; draw off fat.

title: easter salad
directions: Combine and chill.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup crushed walnuts over top.

title: wendy's no knead honey oatmeal bread
directions: In saucepan, heat 1 cup of water to boiling.
Stir in oats, margarine, honey and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and baking soda.
Be sure water is not too hot or it will kill the yeast.
In a large mixing bowl, combine yeast mixture, egg and 2 cups of flour and oat mixture.
Use dough hook and beat until the ingredients are combined and batter is smooth.
By hand, add enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Spread batter into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan and another smaller one.
Smooth tops of loaves. Let rise on top of stove with oven door open at 350° about 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Remove from pans and butter.

title: carrot bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Line with foil.
Grease foil.
In a large bowl, mix flour, walnuts, baking powder and cinnamon.
In a food processor or blender, process oil, brown sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add carrots and process until finely chopped.
Pour over flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 minutes or until edges pull away from sides of pan and a pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan.
Yield:
24 bars.

title: cupcake cheese cakes
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla until sugar is dissolved. Pour small amount (to cover) on top of cheese cakes.
Dab 1/2 to 1 teaspoon favorite canned pie filling on top of each cheese cake and bake 5 minutes at 300°.
Makes 25 to 30.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Begin with 1 cup of starter in nonmetal container.
Never refrigerate it or use any metal with it or seal it airtight.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 16 muffins.

title: chicken burgers
directions: Combine the ingredients and fill hamburger buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Just before serving, heat oven to 350° and heat 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: berry good slush
directions: Spoon half of the yogurt and half of the applesauce into a sandwich size resealable plastic bag.
Pour half of the juice into the bag and seal.
Shake to mix.
Repeat with the remaining ingredients and another bag.
Freeze bags about 35 minutes or until slushy.
Spoon into 2 glasses.
Garnish with strawberries and serve.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken or turkey dressing casserole
directions: Spread chicken over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups and milk together.
Pour over chicken.
Mix dressing according to directions on package and sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dave's famous bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve hot or cold with tortilla chips. If served hot, add some grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with large amounts of cold beer.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat with onion and celery. Add tomatoes and beans. Combine. Add cabbage. Cook on top of stove until cabbage is tender.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pan.
Freeze overnight.
Cut with electric knife and serve.

title: pluket cake
directions: Let bread thaw.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Melt butter or margarine.
Grease angel food cake pan.
Pinch off dough the size of walnuts.
Roll in melted butter, then in sugar mixture.
Place in pan in layers until all dough is used. Sprinkle nuts over each layer of dough balls.
Pour the rest of the butter and sugar mixture over dough balls.
Let raise until double in size. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Turn over on plate and let cool with pan over it.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in Prego, water and spices; simmer.
In small bowl, combine cheese and egg.
In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Thaw spinach in medium bowl. Add eggs, whipping cream, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, tarragon and parsley flakes. Beat slightly.
Place crust in a 9-inch pie plate or pan.
Place spinach along the bottom.
Sprinkle cheese on top of spinach. Pour egg mixture over spinach and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute pepper and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal-honey bread(easy to make and good for you!)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl and pour boiling water over all.
Let cool until lukewarm (approximately 1/2 hour).
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Add flour one cup at a time, mixing well until dough is no longer damp or sticky.
Knead well; cover and let rise until dough becomes double in bulk.
Punch down and divide 4 equal shares.
Shape into loaves, kneading each one.
Let rise in buttered pans until doubled in bulk and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Crush cranberries in meat grinder or cuisenart.
Add sugar and pineapple; stir until sugar dissolves.
Add tub of Cool Whip and stir well.
Then put in fridge for a couple of hours.

title: wonderful coconut cream pie
directions: Prepare and bake a single pie shell. Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt. Gradually add milk. Cook in double boiler until thickened, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Slowly add hot mixture in slightly beaten egg yolks and cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add butter, vanilla and coconut. Pour mixture into cooled pie shell. Top with meringue and bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: butter rolls
directions: On a floured surface, roll out each biscuit into a flat circle approximately 6 inches in diameter. Add butter, sugar and vanilla to center of the circle. Fold dough up around ingredients. Place rolls in a baking pan (about 2 inches deep) with fold against bottom of pan. Pour milk over rolls until half way up on sides of rolls. Bake in 325° oven until tops of biscuits are crispy brown. Serve, spooning milk mixture over rolls.

title: southwest taco dip(makes 1 dozen)
directions: Combine beans, turkey, onion and chili powder in shallow 2-quart microwave dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 8 minutes, stirring to mash beans and break up turkey every 3 minutes until meat is white.
Stir in salsa, sprinkle with cheese and microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add bananas. Mix. Add all dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Very delicious.
This is a soft cookie.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Heat
(simmer) 24 hours.
Can put in cheesecloth filled with allspice tied up.
Keep simmering to keep warm as glasses are filled (drink warm).

title: turkey salad
directions: Cut turkey into bite size pieces.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill before serving.
Serves 5.

title: honey crunch
directions: Toast Quaker oats in a 350° oven on cookie sheet.
Combine, mix and spread on celery sticks.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cut beef in 5 or 6 chunks.
Place in roaster or Dutch oven just big enough for the size of meat.

title: meat and noodles
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off grease and add chicken noodle soup and water.
Cover and let simmer 20 minutes.

title: brazil nut fruit cake
directions: Put nuts, dates, pineapple and cherries into large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nuts and fruits.
Mix with hands until well coated.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add mashed beans to hamburger.
Saut onions, peppers, minced garlic in butter.
Add all ingredients together and simmer for 3 hours.
Crock-pot works good.
Makes about 1 1/2 to 2 gallons.

title: spice or holiday tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients. Store in a covered container. When ready to serve, add 2 tsp. to 1 cup boiling water.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and spread to edge of pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
While hot, cut into 2 x 1-inch pieces to make about 4 dozen.
Serve hot.
Can be made ahead.
Bake only 15 minutes, then freeze.
Reheat about 15 minutes if frozen.

title: ginger tea
directions: Strain tea into pitcher.
Add juice of oranges and lemon.
Add sugar, cracked ice and ginger ale.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and margarine; beat at low speed until crumbly. Stir in nuts. Press 2 3/4 cups of mixture in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 pan. To remaining mixture add balance of ingredients and spoon evenly over base. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream. Makes 12 servings.

title: fruit and juice breakfast shake
directions: Break banana into small pieces and put in blender with pineapple juice, yogurt and strawberries; blend until smooth. Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: layered green salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in deep narrow bowl until 3/4 full. Cover layered salad with salad dressing.
Sprinkle heavily with grated cheese.
Cover with crumbled bacon and chill.
Is crisp and good second day.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix last 6 ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool slightly and pour over drained vegetables.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: nutty party mix
directions: Combine nuts and noodles in a large bowl.
Blend butter, sauces and pour over nuts.
Toss to coat.
Spread on jelly roll pan (single layer) and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Put in a large container and add raisins.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix together in order given and bake at 375° oven for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: earthquake dessert(this is unusual and very good.)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan. (If you use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, you will have runover.) Cover bottom with coconut (as much as you desire), then cover with chopped nuts. Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour over coconut mixture. Combine margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Stir until smooth. Spoon over cake mix; do not stir. Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: In a large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, soda, lemon peel, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and orange extract.
Add this to flour mixture along with zucchini and nuts.
Mix well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans in pan.
Spread coconut over pecans.
Mix cake as directed on box; spread cake mixture over coconut.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and vanilla together.
Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Let cool at least 5 minutes.

title: fruit cup
directions: Peel banana; slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Peel grapefruit and orange; remove membrane.
Cut slices into bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients together, using strawberries and peaches while they are frozen, breaking apart with fork after they are added to other ingredients.
Serve immediately, before frozen fruit is totally thawed.

title: lemon yogurt cookies(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spray cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray or oil lightly.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, salt, mustard, pepper, vinegar and water.
Crumble bacon.
In grease, cook potatoes and onion with mixture for at least 2 hours.

title: sour cream meat casserole
directions: Mix the sour cream, cream cheese and onion; set aside.
Brown the meat, salt, sugar and garlic salt.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook the noodles.
Grease a deep casserole dish.
Layer noodles, sour cream, then meat (2 layers). Top with thin layer of noodles; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions in butter until lightly browned.
In kettle, combine browned onions in butter with bouillon, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Cover and cook on low heat 4 hours.
Top each bowl with toasted French bread, sprinkled with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.
Recipe may be doubled, kept hot and served from slow cooker.

title: broccoli corn bread(delicious!)
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
I put a cup to two cups of cottage cheese and 1 to 2 cups of cheese.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine creamed corn, Niblets, flour, salt, eggs, cream and melted butter.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes more.

title: dana's pineapple  layer cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Mix cake mix as instructed on box. Pour into two 9 inch round pans. Place in oven for appoximately 15-22 minutes. Meanwhile, mix sour cream, well drained pineapple,

and sugar in large bowl. After mixture is blended well, take half of mixture and mix with the container of cool whip. Set both mixtures in the refrigerator until cake is done and completely cooled. Once cake is cooled, take the mixture without the cool whip and spread on top of one of the cakes. Take the other cake and set on top of the first layer. Your mixture should be in between the two layers. Now, take our your Cool Whip mixture and spread all over the cake, like frosting. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve. Enjoy!

title: franks 'n rice
directions: Brown franks in butter in skillet, adding onion the last few minutes.
Saute until onion is tender; add water.
Bring to a boil; stir in salt and rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in catsup and vinegar.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cheese and 3 tablespoons of the pineapple juice together.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Spray a casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Pour pineapple mixture into bottom of dish.
Crush the sleeve of Ritz crackers.
Melt margarine and mix with cracker crumbs until wet.
Spread over pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn souffle
directions: Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring. Bring to a boil.
Add corn and egg yolks.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook 10 minutes or longer.
Fold in egg whites.
Spoon into buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions in half lengthwise first, then in thin slices. In a large pan, heat butter and oil over medium heat.
Add onions, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until onions soften.
Reduce heat and simmer until onions are caramelized, about 45 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Bring to a bubble. Add liquids and simmer 30 minutes.

title: baked pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
In mixing bowl, stir together pecans, salt, Tabasco sauce, soy sauce (optional) and butter. Spread pecans evenly in baking dish and bake for 15-20 minutes.

title: white clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 7 minutes. Serve over pasta.

title: easy go pound cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in bowl; mix with mixer on medium speed until all mixed.
Don't whip!
Turn into cake pan that has been greased and lightly floured (tube pan).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 or 20 minutes.
Makes a crunchy top icing crust.

title: cajun fried turkey
directions: Boil all together except butter until all seasonings are dissolved.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Once cooled, inject mixture into turkey with large cattle syringe.
Sprinkle inside and out with extra Tony C's seasoning.
Refrigerate 24 hours. Heat peanut oil to 275° to 300° in 24-quart stainless steel stockpot.
Use a coat hanger to suspend the turkey in the pot. Cook for 4 minutes per pound plus 5 minutes (12 pound equal 53 minutes).
Oil can be reused for 5 to 7 turkeys, especially if you fry potatoes in between. They are delicious and help clean the oil. Turkey will be juicy and spicy.

title: amish church peanut butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together; stir thoroughly.
Use on bread and crackers.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerettes.
Combine cauliflower, green onions, celery, olives and green peppers in a large bowl. Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss gently.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Remove stem ends from tomatoes.
Remove pulp from each tomato, leaving shell.
Mash tomato pulp.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Fill tomato shell with mixture; place in ungreased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley or additional bacon crumbs.

title: grilled spam
directions: Combine juice and seasonings.
Score luncheon meat on diagonal 1/8 inch deep and 1 inch apart.

title: pork chops with apples and onions
directions: Sear pork chops.
Turn down heat and brown onions in saucepan. Add liquid; simmer 20 minutes.
Add apples and spices.
Simmer another 35 minutes.

title: chinese beets
directions: Add beets, 1 1/2 cups liquid beet juice and all remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat in saucepan until thickened. Cool.
Refrigerate.

title: french chicken
directions: Shake chicken, flour, salt, pepper and paprika in bag.
Fry chicken in olive oil until browned well.
When browned, add onion, cooking sherry and water to chicken and simmer with lid for 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream, mayonnaise and parsley to drippings.
Stir until blended well.
Heat, but do not boil.
Pour over chicken.
Serve.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugars, flour and cocoa. Set aside. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form. Add sugar a little at a time beating until stiff peaks form. Fold in flour mixture. Spoon into an ungreased angel food cake pan. Remove air pockets by running a knife through it. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine. Add egg. Add flour alternately with milk. Add banana. Fold in raisins which have been coated with a little flour.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip squares(microwave)
directions: Cream butter and vanilla.
Add brown sugar gradually, creaming until fluffy.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in half of the chocolate chips.
Turn into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart glass baking dish.
Top with remaining chocolate chips.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 7 to 8 minutes at Medium-high or until edges begin to pull away from the sides of the dish; rotate dish one-quarter turn once.
Set dish on flat surface.
Cool, then cut into squares.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets.
Whisk mayonnaise, sour cream, evaporated milk, oil and vinegar together in a bowl.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Mix warm potatoes with salad dressing, grated vegetables and parsley.
Season with salt and pepper.
Chill overnight.

title: peaches nicole(my daughter's favorite summer dessert.)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash, peel and cut peaches into halves. Remove pits.
Arrange peaches in 2-quart casserole.
Combine honey and lemon juice with 1 cup water.
Pour over peaches. Bake, covered, 30 minutes or until tender. Serve warm or cold with cream poured over.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Combine cake mix, water, sour cream, oil and eggs.
Beat for two minutes.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pans.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup raspberries and 1/3 cup preserves; fold in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Slice each cake layer in half horizontally.
Spread each slice with berry mixture.
Spread top and sides of cake with chocolate frosting.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick crisp pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into a stone crock or jar.
Sprinkle with lime and add enough water to cover.
Allow to sit overnight.
The next morning, rinse cucumbers several times in cold water.
Combine sugar, vinegar and pickling spices in a large container.
Add cucumbers and cook until pickles are crystal clear.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Slice fruit and arrange cream cheese.
Drizzle syrup over and top with nuts.

title: pepperoni balls
directions: Prepare roll mix according to package directions.
But omit 1 egg and use 1 cup of water instead.
Dough does not need to rise.

title: chicken or beef soup(brodo di pollo)
directions: Rinse chicken thoroughly
with
salt.
Place
in
large saucepan with water.
Should
cover
chicken by 3-inches.
Add onion and bring to boil.
Skim
surface of soup with spoon and discard.
After no more foam
appears,
add
the
rest
of the ingredients.
Lower to a medium boil and simmer for 2 hours or until chicken is tender
to
fork.
Remove
chicken and strain broth.
You may debone and cut
up
chicken to add to broth or set aside for chicken salad.
Makes
8 to 10 servings.
Variation: This broth can be
used
over rice, noodles and various other shapes of pasta.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine the cucumbers, salt and sliced onions.
Add ice cubes; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain and rinse thoroughly.
Combine the vinegar, seasonings and sugar; boil.
Add cucumbers and onions. Heat to simmering.
Pack hot.
Avoid boiling, as it softens pickles.
Seal while hot.
Yields 12 to 13 pints.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Cook cut up fryer in salty water until tender; take out 1 cup of broth and let cool until lukewarm.
Take 3 cups of flour and add the lukewarm broth; break 1 large egg and mix into a ball of dough.
When kneaded until quite stiff, roll until very thin and cover with wax paper.
Let it set for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Cut and drop into boiling chicken.
When done, add butter and milk.

title: corn loaves
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray mini-loaf pans with nonstick spray. In medium bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in milk, oil and egg; beat until smooth.
Fold in corn, chilies and jalapenos and pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Makes 6 loaves.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Bake sugar cookie dough on cookie sheet.
Spread out with fingers, reaching all corners of pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Let cool.

title: sausage and noodle casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in large skillet; add onion and green pepper. Cook over medium heat until meat is browned and vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Combine soup and water.
Add meat mixture, noodles, salt and pepper; mix well. Spoon mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix all.
Batter will be stiff.
Fold in blueberries. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix yellow cake mix, oil, eggs and orange juice in a large bowl. Cut mandarin oranges into thirds and fold into cake batter. Bake in 350° oven for type of cake pan on cake box.

title: zucchini no one will recognize(hand me down)
directions: Grate zucchini.
Cook for 5 minutes on top of range (do not add liquid).
Drain well; add butter and sour cream.
Season with salt and pepper.
When cooking, stir and watch carefully as zucchini will burn very easily.
This is a good way to use overgrown zucchini from your garden.
If using very large zucchini, please peel and seed before grating and measuring.

title: dilly bread
directions: Heat cottage cheese, shortening and salt until melted.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese in the center of each chicken piece.
Sprinkle evenly with parsley and pepper.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with wooden picks.
Dip each chicken breast in egg; coat well with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet; brown chicken on all sides.
Remove chicken to a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, reserving drippings in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients to reserved drippings and stir well.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well the sugar and cinnamon.
Mix sugar and cinnamon mixture in apples.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix over apples.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pecan delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 8-inch pie pan. Break crackers without crumbling and mix with pecans; set aside. Begin beating egg whites at high speed in medium bowl; gradually add sugar and continue beating until slightly less than stiff, about 10 minutes total mixing time. Gently fold in pecan mixture with rubber spatula until well covered. Spoon directly into pie pan. Bake for 20 minutes. Pie should be light brown and top will crack while cooling. When completely cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix together oatmeal, syrup, butter and vanilla; pat down in a well-greased pan so it is about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 350° until light brown, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overbake!

title: marshmallow wreaths
directions: Melt butter or margarine and marshmallows together.
Then add cornflakes.
Add green food coloring.
Shape like a wreath on wax paper to cool.
Garnish with red cinnamon.
Good at Christmas.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in tightly covered container until ready to use. Measure 2 teaspoons of mix per cup of hot water.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Boil chicken until tender and remove from bone.
Saute chopped onions and bell peppers in butter.
Cook spaghetti until done, drain.
Add melted cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chicken to spaghetti.
Mix well.
Add peas and fold in easily.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered.
This works well in the crock-pot.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and bacon bits.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°, then broil a few minutes until light brown on top.

title: mccall's microwave herb-roasted chicken
directions: With knife, vent rice packets.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, just until thawed.
In medium bowl, toss rice with celery, onion and parsley.
In small glass bowl, microwave butter on High for 20 seconds or just until softened, not melted.
Stir lemon juice, tarragon, rosemary and thyme into butter; mix well.

title: carrot-pineapple delight
directions: Sift together into a mixing bowl sifted all-purpose flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, ground cinnamon and salt.
Add oil, egg, finely shredded carrots, crushed pineapple with juice and vanilla.
Mix until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick spray coating.
Pour batter evenly into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center of the cake comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Frost with Light Cream Cheese Topping.
Yields 9 (2-ounce) servings.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese slices, and mix lightly.
