Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Remove loaf from oven; cut each cheese slice in triangle and arrange overlapping on top of loaf.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onions and chilies.
Cook hamburger meat; add chili powder.
Dip flour tortillas in hot oil.
Roll hamburger meat topped with sour cream mixture and sprinkle cheese in flour shells.
Secure with toothpicks.
Bake in a 400° oven until brown.

title: old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Stir in milk, water and vanilla.

title: corn soup with crab
directions: Bring broth to a boil in saucepan over moderate heat. Add corn. Cook, stirring, for 3 minutes. Add crab slowly, stirring constantly. Beat eggs with a small amount of water. Add slowly, stirring vigorously. Season with salt.
May thicken soup with 1 tablespoon cornstarch mixed with 1/2 cup water if soup is too thin. Serve in bowls.
Sprinkle onions on top. Serve with soy sauce.

title: joe's lasagna(with just a touch of irish; used at john's river)
directions: In medium size, nonstick skillet, saute ground meat and onion until onion is tender and meat browned.
Do not add fat or oil to skillet.
Add tomato sauce, basil, parsley, oregano, garlic, pepper and mushrooms to ground meat mixture.
Combine well drained spinach with cottage cheese.
Cook 1/2 pound noodles in boiling water until tender and drain.
Lightly oil an 8 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange in layers, beginning with 1/2 of the noodles on bottom.
Spread a layer of the spinach mixture, then the meat mixture, then some grated Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Yield:
6 servings; approximately 405 calories per serving.

title: peanut butter-chocolate brownies
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix together sugar, brown sugar, flour, baking powder and salt. Combine two mixtures and stir well.

title: fish or onion ring batter
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Deep fry in really hot oil. If doing fish, sprinkle fish with flour first so batter will stick.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and sugar over medium heat at a slow boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pineapple and lemon juice.
Then cook on slow for another 5 minutes.
Add jello mix and mix well and pour into sterilized jars.
Seal and refrigerate.
Makes 5 pints.

title: virginia's chili
directions: Brown the hamburger meat in a skillet.
Drain.
Pour into a pan and add water.
Boil for about 10 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, seasoning and chili beans.
Let this mixture cook for about 15 minutes.
Take a potato masher and mash mixture up, while still on stove cooking.
Turn burner to low and simmer for 20 more minutes.
Stir often.
If mixture gets too thick, add more water. Chili is best thick.
A good side dish with this is sliced cheese, sweet pickles and onions.

title: quick cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large soup pot, cooking meat until it turns colors first.
Cook until desired thickness. Serve with French bread or corn bread.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Refrigerate in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Serves 12.

title: wild rose petal candies
directions: Wash petals in cool water and let dry.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Brush petals with egg whites and sprinkle with the sugar. Let dry on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: delicious potato doughnuts
directions: In a large bowl combine potatoes, sugar, buttermilk and eggs. Stir in butter, soda, nutmeg, salt and enough flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and pat to 3/4 inch thickness. cut with a 2 1/2 inch floured doughnut cutter. Using an electric skillet, heat one inch of oil to 350 degrees. Fry the doughnuts for 2 minutes per side or until brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate mounds
directions: Mix above ingredients. Shape into balls. Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Steak should be 1 inch thick.
Pare and quarter the potatoes. Peel and quarter the carrots.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Place 24 x 18-inch piece heavy duty aluminum foil in baking dish.
Place meat on foil and onion soup mix.
Stir together mushroom.
Spread soup on top of steak.
Top with vegetables.
Fold foil over and seal securely.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan, sprayed with no-stick cooking spray.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and tender.
Stir occasionally.
Mix all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add cooked potatoes.
Mix lightly.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Brown the pecans in 2 tablespoons of butter; cool.
Beat eggs; gradually add sugar.
Add condensed milk and instant pudding.
Add nuts and milk to fill freezer (for a 1-gallon freezer of ice cream).

title: cranberry tea
directions: Cover cranberries with water; boil and drain off 4 times. Strain.
(Or use double the amount of water and boil twice.)
To water, add orange juice and lemonade.
Boil together 4 cups water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine both mixtures and serve hot. Makes about 1 gallon.
May be made ahead and heat 1 cup at a time.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Beat eggs into butter mixture.
Stir in flour, salt and nuts.
Chill 30 minutes.
Roll into 1-inch ball.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Grease a cookie sheet at 400°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine.
Melt margarine.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper and grease sides of pan with margarine.
Mold into tube pan. Put in refrigerator for about 2 hours before you remove from pan. After cake has been removed, you must keep refrigerated.
If covered, cake will keep for several weeks.

title: braves hot dog chilli
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Cook onion and pepper in a little oil.
Combine all remaining ingredients together with meat, green pepper and onions.
Put in large pot.
Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Boil hot dogs and toast buns.
Serve chilli over hot dogs.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Leave cream cheese out to soften.
Drain pineapple.
Pour boiling water over gelatin; add the ice cubes and stir until soft-set.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple together and set aside. Whip the Avoset, then combine the cheese and pineapple mixture to the gelatin.
Mix well.
Fold in the Avoset and marshmallows. Pour into a mold and refrigerate to set.

title: banana snack cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk, bananas and vanilla; mix well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Stir in flour, oats, soda and salt; mix well.
Stir in chips.
Spread batter into prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: layered lettuce
directions: Tear clean, crisp lettuce into small bite size pieces and place in dish.
Layer rest of ingredients in order listed.
Add sugar to mayo and spread over top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours and toss at serving time.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix ingredients; make into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for approximately 10 minutes.

title: casey's delicious white bread
directions: Combine water, milk powder, oil, sugar and salt in the mixing bowl.
Mix ingredients slowly.
Sprinkle yeast over mixture in mixing bowl.
Let it melt into mixture while you sift flour.
Add half (2 cups) of the flour to mixture and beat well for 2 minutes. Slowly add the remaining flour, little by little, until the dough leaves the sides of the bowl, leaving it clean.
Flour a counter and knead until smooth and satiny.
Place dough in a bowl sprayed with Pam.
Turn the dough upside down in the bowl, greasing the side that is up.
Put some plastic wrap over the bowl and put it in the sun or in a warm spot until the dough is doubled in size (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll into 1 large or 2 small balls.
May be rolled in chopped pecans and/or parsley, if desired.
Chill and serve.

title: sausage and spinach soup
directions: Spray saucepot with cooking spray (like Pam); add sausage and cook until brown.
Add broth, onion, carrot and oregano; heat to a boil.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in spinach and cook 1 minute longer.
Serves 5.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans; put in large Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip; put on cooled crust, then put on fresh peaches.
Boil for 2 minutes sugar, cornstarch, jello and water.
Cool until jelled a little, then pour over peaches. Refrigerate.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Cut chicken, place in soup pot.
Add the water and onion. Bring to a boil, cook on medium until liquid is reduced by one third.
Add the rice and seasoning.
Cook approximately 20 minutes more.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper; drain.
Combine ground beef mixture with rice, tomatoes and chili powder.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine. Place in a square pan.
Mix Dream Whip by directions on box.
Also mix vanilla and cream cheese.
Whip and put on top of graham cracker crumbs.
Put 2 cans cherry pie filling on top of Dream Whip mixture.

title: chewy chocolate macaroons(yields 8 dozen)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Drop 1-inch apart on well-greased baking sheet.
(Can use Pam.) Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain well.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add applesauce, flour and spices.
Put soda in boiling water until dissolved.
Add to mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish hash
directions: Cook the onion in the margarine in a frying pan on medium heat.
Then add meat and potatoes.
This should be nicely browned, but not dry.
Season to taste.
This is good served with eggs.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Mix white and brown sugar together.
Mix milk and stir until well blended.
Add butter and bring to boil until thick.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 400 for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients, then drop onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins in 1 cup water over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain liquid to make 1/2 cup.
(Let cool.)
Cream butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in a 1/2 cup liquid. Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to the butter-sugar mixture; then add oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: my mom's love cake
directions: Line bowl with 1/2 of cake.
Put one layer of glaze, one layer of pudding (mixed up with milk) and one layer of Cool Whip. Repeat layers; top with strawberries after Cool Whip on top.
Put in fridge for about 2 hours before serving.
Serve with love! Serves 12.

title: praline grahams
directions: Line a 15 x 10 baking pan with heavy duty foil. Layer graham crackers in pan. In saucepan, combine butter & brown sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Carefully pour over crackers. Sprinkle with almonds. Bake at 400 degrees for 6-8 minutes. Cut each cracker into 4 sections. Transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

title: steamed pork chop dinner
directions: Brown pork chops in oil in a large, heavy skillet with tight fitting lid.
Drain off excess oil.
Add beans with liquid; layer potatoes, then onion.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.
Cook slowly, covered.
When water is gone, potatoes and chops should be done.
Serves four.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, green onions, pepper, celery and peas in a large salad bowl.
Spread salad dressing over peas.
Sprinkle sugar over salad dressing.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top of salad dressing.
Sprinkle bacon over cheese.

title: geraldine's cole slaw with cooked dressing
directions: Make alternate layers of onion and cabbage in a bowl. Sprinkle with scant 3/4 cup sugar or less.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: 1. Beat egg in bowl. Stir in milk and oil.
2. Stir in remaining ingredients except chips. Stir until
just moistened. Fold in chips.
3. Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake until golden brown, about 20
minutes. Immediately remove from pan.

title: sara's fruit salad
directions: Mix juice and fruit. Sprinkle lemon pudding over fruit and mix. Chill overnight. Just before serving, dice 1 banana and add to fruit.

title: fruit slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.

title: family favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add alternately with milk to the creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until lightly brown.
Yield:
about 5 dozen.
These cookies freeze well.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook
meat
and
onion until well done, drain, add salt and pepper
to
taste.
In a large saucepan, melt shortening. Add flour
and
brown slightly over low heat, stirring often. Add enchilada
mix
sauce,
tomato sauce, water and seasoning mix. Stir constantly until thick and hot, add salt.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place beef cubes and soup bones in a 4 to 6-quart pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and cook at a slow boil for 1 hour to make beef stock.
Then cut up and add cabbage, then add diced onion, tomatoes and tomato sauce, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and cook at a slow boil for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add pumpkin, eggs and dry ingredients. Drop by tablespoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together the last 4 ingredients.
Skin chicken.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over chicken and bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Turn pieces over and pour rest of mixture over chicken and bake another 45 minutes.

title: laura's rice pudding
directions: Bring to a boil the water with the cinnamon stick.
Add rice (while stirring).
When it comes to a boiling point again, cover, turn fire low and simmer about 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Add sugar and cook, uncovered, a minute longer.
Add evaporated milk and raisins; continue to cook until thick, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking to bottom of pan.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage until tender, drain and then carefully separate leaves from stem.
Combine meat, onions, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
On each cabbage leaf, place several spoons of the mixture.
Secure with a toothpick and place in a casserole dish. Mix tomato sauce and water; pour over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: batter buns
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast until dissolved.
Add milk, egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat with mixer to a soft dough.
Add rest of flour.
Stir with wooden spoon. Cover; let rise until double, about 30 minutes.
Punch down and shape into rolls; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hiking bread
directions: Lightly spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with Pam.
Combine flours, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a medium bowl.
In a large bowl, beat yogurt, brown sugar and molasses until smooth.
Add oats and mix well.
Add flour and raisins to combine.
The batter is very dry and it takes a little work to mix in all the flour.
Put in loaf pan and let rest 20 minutes.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned and edges have begun to pull away from the sides of the pan.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Do not stir until all ingredients are in mixing bowl together. Bake at 400° approximately 1/2 hour.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1/2 cup butter until tender.
Combine onion, soup, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, almonds and broccoli.
Mix well.
Spoon into 2 lightly greased 2-quart casseroles.
Combine stuffing mix and 1/2 cup butter.
Spoon over broccoli mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt margarine and mix all other ingredients, except the cereal.
Pour the mixture over the cereal and mix well.
Put in double paper bag.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Turn over and bake for 1/2 hour.
Take out and let cool.
Great for after school snacks.

title: cracker candy
directions: Cover a large cookie sheet with foil and place crackers on foil.
Set aside.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter and add brown sugar.
Let come to a boil and boil exactly 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and pour over crackers, spreading evenly.
Place in 400° oven for exactly 5 minutes.
In the meantime, melt chocolate bark in microwave.
Remove crackers from oven and spread chocolate bark evenly over crackers.
Allow to cool.
Remove foil from the bottom of crackers and break in pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Can be frozen.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour, sifted together with soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Stir in coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites, beaten until fluffy.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae dessert
directions: Melt butter in microwave on High for 1 minute.
Combine vanilla wafer crumbs, pecans and butter, mixing well.
Press half of crumb mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Spread ice cream evenly over crust.
Press remaining crumb mixture over ice cream. Cover and freeze until firm.
To serve, cut into squares and top each with chocolate sauce.
Yields 15 servings.

title: peanut butter pizza
directions: Cream the peanut butter, butter, sugars, egg and vanilla together.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt; add to the first mixture.
Press onto a lightly greased pizza pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate or butterscotch chips and miniature marshmallows. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix Velveeta, cream cheese and pimentos until thoroughly mixed.
Form in ball shape and roll in pecans and parsley.
Chill and serve with crackers on side.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let chill until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Knead it good.
Form into balls and bake at 350° for about 10 or 15 minutes until done, but not hard.

title: biscuits
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Combine milk, oil and food coloring.
Add to dry ingredients all at once stirring until dough clings together.
Knead 8 times.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with doughnut cutter, saving holes.

title: cookies
directions: Melt bits over hot water, then mix together.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper and let stand.

title: basque chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle chicken with mixed peppers and saute in oil in large skillet over medium heat until golden brown on both sides (about 8 minutes).
Remove chicken and set aside.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add ham, onion and red peppers to skillet; saute 3 to 5 minutes until ham begins to brown and vegetables begin to soften.
Add garlic and rice; cook 1 minute until rice is coated with oil and begins to turn translucent.
Stir in broth and wine. Return chicken to skillet.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes until most liquid is absorbed.
Stir in peas and olives.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes until peas are heated through.
Stir in parsley and Tabasco.
Add salt to taste.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter; boil for 1 minute.
Pour boiled mixture over peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Drop by rounded teaspoons on wax paper or foil.

title: oven-fried chicken(light)
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine cornflake crumbs and parsley; set aside.
In another bowl, combine yogurt, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Brush chicken with yogurt mixture, then sprinkle with crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pita bread
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
With fingers, blend shortening into yeast mixture until almost dissolved.
Stir together the flour and salt.
Add yeast mixture to flour mixture.

Work dough with hands in the bowl until dough is no longer sticky, adding additional water or flour as needed. Transfer dough to a greased bowl, turning once to grease surface. Cover; let dough stand in a warm place 30 to 40 minutes until doubled.
Divide dough into 24 pieces.
With floured hands, work pieces into very smooth balls.
Place on a floured surface. Cover and let rest 20 minutes.
Using fingers, gently flatten balls without creasing dough, keeping them rounded.
On a well floured surface, lightly roll 1 piece of dough at a time to a 7-inch circle, turning dough a quarter turn once (do not stretch, puncture or crease dough).
Place 2 rounds on an ungreased baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake about 3 to 4 minutes or until dough is puffed and set.
Turn pita rounds over with spatula. Bake about 2 minutes more or until light brown.
Repeat with remaining dough, baking 1 batch before rolling and baking the next.
Cool on wire racks.

title: marinade of fresh dill
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in margarine and add sweet potatoes. Add enough milk to make dough stiff enough to roll.
Cut biscuits and place on greased baking sheet. Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Butter pan.
In a heavy saucepan combine sugar, cocoa, salt, syrup and Milnot; cook, stirring constantly, to soft ball stage. Add vanilla and butter.
Cool for a few minutes.
Beat the fudge until it turns a dull color and pour into buttered pan.
Serves 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in whipped cream and fruits.
Pour in refrigerator trays and freeze several hours. Serves 10 to 12.

title: venison and noodles
directions: Brown venison "shaved" slices.
Saute onion and garlic powder. Add beef stew seasoning mix and paprika; simmer until tender. Add peppers and celery.

title: custard pie
directions: Roll out pastry; line pan.
Scald milk over hot water, in top of double boiler, or on very low heat.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Add scalded milk slowly to egg mixture, stirring.
Pour custard into pastry-lined pan.
Bake at 425° for ten minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 25 minutes.

title: pork chops with apples and onions
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Rub sage onto both sides of meat.
Spray 12-inch skillet with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Preheat skillet. Cook chops for 5 minutes; turn.
Add onion to skillet.
Cook mixture for 5 to 7 minutes more or until no pink remains in chops. Remove chops and keep warm, leaving onions in skillet.

title: not-so-sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add ketchup, garlic powder and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon onto your hamburger buns. Serves.
Makes 4.

title: pork chops and potatoes
directions: Place potatoes and onions in 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Top with pork chops. Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: stuffed clams(24 shells)
directions: Divide clams evenly in bottom of shells.
Mix next 4 ingredients and juice.
Cover clams in shells with crumb mixture. Top with additional small pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After first 15 minutes, sprinkle with Sauterne, if desired.
Bake remaining 5 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute butter and onions in a small saucepan, then add to potatoes.
Pour in cream of celery soup, milk and celery salt. Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat and serve.
Tastes great with Cheez Whiz.

title: turkey and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli in 10 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, mushrooms, chicken or turkey and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli. Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Mix with herb seasoned stuffing mix and 1 cup chicken broth or milk.
Pour over other mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cook onions in butter; add sauerkraut with cut up apple and 2 bay leaves; add wine and sugar.
Cook for 1 hour (no water).
Cook 1 day before and warm up.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease or spray a 9x13 inch baking dish.
Toss bread cubes into bottom.
Combine meat, eggs, milk, mustard and pepper.
Pour over bread.
Top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and bake about 1 hour at 350°, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 10-12.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Simply mix all ingredients, except for the grated cheese, together in a large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Form mixture into a ball and roll the cheese ball in the grated Cheddar cheese. The Cheddar cheese coats the cheese ball.
Chill about 1 hour. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: sauteed chicken strips
directions: Cut the chicken breasts crosswise into 1/2 inch wide strips. In a small bowl, combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Toss the chicken strips in the seasoned flour to coat lightly.
Set the chicken aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter in the oil over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken pieces and stir-fry until the chicken just begins to brown, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add the grapes, chicken broth, cream and wine.
Let mixture come to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and simmer, stirring often, until chicken is cooked through and the grapes are slightly softened, 3 to 4 minutes.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping mix
with
cup
of the milk and vanilla in large mixer bowl.
Beat on high with electric mixer about 6 minutes or
until
topping
thickens
and forms peaks. Add remaining milk and pie filling mix; blend on low.
Beat on high 2 minutes,
scraping
bowl
occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell. Refrigerate at least
hours.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gold'n nut crunch
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Mix nuts and margarine in medium bowl until well coated.
Add cheese, garlic powder, oregano and celery salt; toss until well coated.
Spread in ungreased jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes.
Stir in cereal; cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: stewed shrimp a la creole
directions: Remove shells, wash shrimp thoroughly and drain.
Brown flour in hot
fat.
Add onion, then shrimp, cooking until pink and slightly
brown and stirring constantly.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients and
bring to a boil.
Cover, lower heat and simmer for	20 minutes.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain off water and cool.
Cut up ingredients and mix together.
Put 1/2 dressing on salad and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Add other 1/2 dressing when serving.
Amounts of ingredients can be juggled until you get it how you like it.

title: pig pickens cake
directions: Make frosting first and let it chill.
The ingredients are: pudding, pineapple, powdered sugar, coconut and Cool Whip.
Mix the first 4 ingredients and chill.
While cake is baking, add Cool Whip to this mixture when you are ready to frost the cake.

title: clay recipe for christmas ornaments(oven drying method)
directions: If dough is too dry, work in another tablespoon of water with your hands.

title: oreo mousse
directions: Crush cookies 5 to 10 at a time in a Ziploc bag (kids love to do this).
Put in bowl; add whipped topping and fold together.
Serve as dessert plain or with graham crackers.

title: cold cucumber, sour cream salad
directions: Peel, slice in half lengthwise and de-seed the cucumbers. Sprinkle generously with salt and let sit for 30 minutes.
Rinse cucumbers in running water to remove salt and pat dry.
Slice cucumbers into 1/8-inch slices.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: In a glass bowl, combine vinegar and mustard; allow to stand overnight.
The next day, place the eggs in the top of a double boiler and beat slightly.
Add the sugar and beat smooth.
Beat in the vinegar-mustard mixture.
Cook over simmering water until the mustard has thickened and begins to bubble in the middle. Transfer to an electric mixer bowl and beat for 5 minutes.
Add the salt and stir.
Pour into jars and store in the refrigerator. Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients and fry until brown.

title: peanut butter mousse pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Mix peanut butter and cream cheese until well blended. Add sugars and milk.
Continue mixing until fluffy. Fold in whipped topping and mix thoroughly.
Pour into cooled pie crust and chill in freezer for 2 hours (or until set). Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for several hours before serving.
Great on Triscuits.

title: easy wings
directions: Put frozen wings in two 13 x 9-inch pans.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; turn wings.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: mock souffle(chicken casserole)
directions: Cut bread in cubes.
Save buttered cubes for top of casserole. Place half the plain bread cubes in bottom of casserole.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; spread this on top of bread layer.
Cover with other half of bread cubes. Beat eggs and milk; pour over the bread cubes.
(Here the mixture may be chilled for later completion.)
Add soup.
Cover with buttered bread cubes.
Add the grated cheese the last few minutes of cooking.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes (350° if the dish is deep).

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, vanilla and cream.
Keep out some sugar to put on spreading board or waxed paper to roll candy. Roll out sugar mixture thin and flat.
Spread with peanut butter (your preference, thick or thin).
Roll up gently. Cover with aluminum foil and put in freezer about 2 hours.
Then slice and eat.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, save drippings.
Remove bacon, crumble and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Combine with beans, brown sugar, mustard, catsup and Worcestershire sauce. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil.
Then add cut up toamtoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered. Add remaining ingredients and cook covered for 20 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: *Butter pecan, butterscotch, chocolate, milk chocolate, chocolate fudge, French vanilla or vanilla can be used.

title: cashew pea salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, juice and dill until well blended.
Add all remaining ingredients except cashews; mix well.
Refrigerate. Sprinkle with cashews just before serving.
Makes 6 cups.

title: quick fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter.
Add wine and sour cream; melt together.
Add Parmesan.
Remove from heat as it begins to boil.
Serve over cooked fettucini noodles.

title: st. patrick's day salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add pineapple.
Cool until syrupy. Then add 7-Up, marshmallows and bananas and let set in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix butter, sugar, flour and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick and let cool.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
When gelatin is firm, spread topping over it.
Grated cheese may be sprinkled on, if desired.

title: blueberry puddin' pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate with halved ladyfingers or cookies.
Cook pudding according to directions, using 3 cups of milk; add orange rind while it is cooking.
Stir in coconut.
Chill.
Stir well and spoon 1/2 of mixture into pie pan. Spread 1/2 or more of the blueberries.
Cover with remaining pudding.
Whip heavy cream with sugar and vanilla until stiff; spoon cream on pie.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: debbie's chex mix
directions: Bake at 250° for 2 hours. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: fishing worms and june bugs
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter in pan.
Toss noodles and marshmallows in a bowl.
Pour melted peanut butter over noodles and drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Put in refrigerator (work up quickly).

title: granny's egg custard pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add the sugar and flour; mix well.
Add the butter, milk and vanilla extract; mix well.
Set aside.
Wash beaters.
Beat egg whites in a separate bowl; fold into first mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, butter, vanilla, flour and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until light brown.
Roll hot cookies in additional confectioners sugar.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: chicken en casserole
directions: Clean chicken and cut the chicken into pieces convenient for serving.

Melt the butter in a small frying pan, add the onion and carrot, both cut in thin slices, also the pieces of chicken, and cook all until golden brown, placing them in the casserole as they reach this stage.
Pour the stock over them, put in the bay leaf, and cover closely.
When nearly done, add the potatoes sliced, the mushrooms and seasoning.
Cover, and finish the cooking.
Add the sherry at the last moment before serving, and send to table in casserole.

title: pineapple zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.

title: crisp spiced nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a bowl with an electric mixer, beat whites with salt until very foamy and gradually beat in sugar, Worcestershire sauce, paprika and cayenne.
Stir in nuts and butter, combining well, and spread in a large shallow baking pan. Bake nuts in middle of oven, stirring every 10 minutes, until crisp and golden, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Spread nuts on a sheet of foil and cool.
Break up nut clusters.
Nuts may be made 1 week ahead and kept in an airtight container at room temperature. Makes about 4 1/2 cups.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate, butter and salt together in a double boiler. Add sugar, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring after each addition.
Add milk, a little at a time, until well mixed.
Can serve hot over ice cream or put in container in refrigerator and cool to serve cool over ice cream.
If you are a chocoholic, you will love this!

title: brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture and vanilla; add nuts last.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill overnight.
This makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add beaten eggs, sweet milk and butter.
Cook on stove on low heat.
Stir while cooking. When thick enough, pour into baked pie shells.
Beat 3 egg whites. Add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie and brown lightly in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients. Roll into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Peel and grate zucchini.
Add lemon juice.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add sugar, pectin and pineapple.
Bring to boil.
Boil 6 minutes. Add jello.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain juice from beans into soup and mix well.
In a 1-quart casserole dish, put a thin layer of beans, a layer of onion rings and a layer of soup mixture.
Repeat layers until all is gone. Put a few onion rings on the top.
Bake at 450° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Sprinkle soy sauce, sherry, ginger and cornstarch over chicken; stir and set aside.
Choose several vegetables for stir-fry. Stir-fry each vegetable separately in 1 tablespoon oil for 1 to 2 minutes.
Set all aside in another pan (or serving dish) as you finish.
Stir-fry chicken in 2 tablespoons oil until cooked.
Add juice from vegetables (if there is any).
Add 1/4 cup water and the chicken bouillon granules to make sauce.
Stir vegetables in to reheat.
When finished, stir in the cashews.
Serve over rice.

title: asparagus on cheese toast
directions: Butter and toast bread; as many is needed.
Slice into 2 triangles.
Grate cheese (any type) and serve on top.
Cook asparagus in the juices.
Serve.
Let each person put their own serving together; toast-asparagus.
Top with cheese.

title: tex mex catfish fajitas
directions: Pat fish dry.
Place in non-metallic dish.
Stir together pepper flakes, lime juice and oregano and pour over fish. Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Wrap tortillas in foil and warm while broiling fish on nonstick baking sheet.
Arrange fish in single layer.
Broil 4 inches from broiler 5 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork, turning only thicker pieces.
Divide fish evenly among tortillas, arranging fish down center of each.
Top with sour cream and salsa.
Fold over bottom and 2 sides to enclose filling.

title: cinnamon raisin oat triangles
directions: Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in butter until evenly mixed.
Remove 1 cup of crumb mixture and set aside.
Pat remaining mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine soup, chilies, sour cream, onion tops (reserve 1/4 cup), olives, onion, cumin and 1/2 grated cheese.
Set aside 1/2 mixture.
Add chicken to other 1/2 mixture.
Place 3 heaping tablespoonfuls in each tortilla and roll up.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Pour on other 1/2 of sauce mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and green onion tops.
Also sprinkle with additional cumin and paprika.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain excess fat. Add taco seasoning mix and 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook at least 5 minutes. Add tomato sauce and cooked rice.
Spoon into a baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until it bubbles.
Immediately before serving, add broken taco chips to top of casserole.
Yield: 8 servings.
Serve with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: brownies
directions: Beat the butter and sugar together until it has a creamy texture; beat in the two eggs, add the vanilla.
Stir in the flour and the chocolate, then you may add nuts if you wish to.
Bake at 350°.

title: caesar salad
directions: *Salad may be a head of lettuce, watercress, bibb lettuce, endive or romaine.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Wash strawberries.
Cut in half and dry.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie filling
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into bottom crust.
Dot with butter. Place top crust.
Vent, flute and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
First heat pecan kernels in a buttered pan and spread evenly.
Boil first four ingredients until it turns golden brown.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over pecans in pan. Spread thin.
Break in pieces.

title: frosted apricot drink
directions: Press apricots through sieve.
Mix pulp and milk.
Put ice cream in a pitcher.
Pour milk over ice cream.
Stir until slightly mixed.

title: hobo bread
directions: Dissolve yeast into 1/2 cup (lukewarm) water, add sugar, ginger, milk, shortening, and salt to water.
Mix in flour 1 cup at a time with wooden spoon.
Divide butter into 2 or 3 coffee cans.
Put the lids on the cans and set in a warm place to rise until the lids pop off.
Bake without lids for 45 minutes at 350° in center of oven.

title: doris' pineapple stuffing
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toast bread and cut into cubes.
Beat eggs.
Blend sugar and butter together.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix together creamed ingredients, bread cubes and pineapple with juice and put into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serve with ham.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix cheese, spinach, egg and seasonings.
Grease a 13 x 9 pan. Layer 1/2 cup of sauce, 1/3 of noodles and half of cheese mixture. Repeat.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edge.
Cover tightly.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce made out of 1 pound Velveeta cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes.

title: gooey butter cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine ingredients and mix well. Pat into a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking pan. Prepare Filling.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Layer pecans and coconut in bottom of lightly greased pan. Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix together cream cheese, melted butter and confectioners sugar.
Drizzle over cake mix.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown turkey meat.
Add tomato sauce, onion, spices and hot sauce.
Place in tacos and add lettuce, tomatoes and cheese. Equals 4 proteins, 1 bread, 2 3/4 vegetables and 1/4 milk.

title: raisin honey chews
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, honey, egg and peel.
Stir in flour, soda, salt and
oats.
Beat well.
Add raisins.

title: sausage cake
directions: Bring raisins and water to a boil and cool.
Measure 1 cup raisin juice (add water if not enough).
Mix raisin juice, sausage and sugar until well blended.
Sift flour, soda and spices into sausage mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix. Put in tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Allow to cool. Keep refrigerated.
Don't overbake.

title: microwave french onion soup
directions: In 2-quart casserole, cook onions in margarine on High 8 to 10 minutes or until onions are very tender, stirring once.
Stir in beef broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High about 8 minutes.
Spoon into bowls.
Top each serving with croutons and cheese.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, floating fruit on top as garnish.

title: chicken and rice(for microwave cooking-an easy family meal)
directions: In
quart
glass casserole, blend rice, onion, soup, hot water,
green pepper and salt.
Arrange chicken with large ends around edges and small
in
center over rice.
Brush each piece with butter.
Sprinkle
with
paprika and garlic powder. Microwave (High) covered, 30
to 35 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking,
rest,
covered
minutes.
Check rice/chicken for doneness.
Add a few minutes, more if needed. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lynn's favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, add peanut butter.
Add sugar gradually, then add well beaten egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet, lightly greased.
Flatten with fork that has been dipped in flour; make crisscrosses on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: tomato-pepper thighs
directions: Remove skin from thighs.
In medium pan over medium-high heat, brown chicken in patches in oil for 5 minutes, turning once. Remove to plate.
Add onions, peppers and pepper flakes to the drippings left in the pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, olives and salt.
Stir mixture to break up tomatoes.
Return chicken to pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 15 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove cover and on high heat, boil until sauce is reduced slightly.

title: raisin spice cookies(diabetic)
directions: In a saucepan combine 2/3 cup water, shortening, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool until pan is just warm on the bottom.
Combine liquid sweetener and 2 tablespoons water.
Add to raisin mixture.
Stir in egg and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until barely soft to touch.
Remove and let cool.
Makes 2 dozen.
Each cookie is 56 calories.

title: baked stew
directions: No need to brown meat.
Place meat and vegetables in roasting pan.
Mix V-8 juice, salt, pepper, sugar and tapioca together. Pour over meat and vegies.
You can use peas, carrots, mushrooms, etc.
Bake in oven at 250° for 5 hours (covered).
Stir at midway and taste.

title: twice baked potatoes deluxe
directions: Prepare and bake potatoes in preheated 400 oven for 1 hour. While still hot, slice each potato in half lengthwise.
Scoop pulp carefully into large mixing bowl, leaving a thin shell.
Mash potatoes; add salt, pepper, margarine and milk as needed.
Stir in onion, Cheddar and Jack cheeses and spinach.
Spoon potato mixture back into the shells.
Either bake at 400° for 20 minutes and serve; or until lightly browned; or freeze, wrapped individually in wax paper, then placed in Ziploc freezer bag.
Remove as many as needed.
Bake as before.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rice and shrimp salad
directions: Mix and garnish with green peppers.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3/4 cup boiling water. Add cold water or juice with ice to make 1 1/4 cups. After Jell-O is syrupy, add pineapple, celery, carrot and raisins. Each 1/2 cup serving equals 25 calories.

title: the best white clam sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients (clams with juice, do not drain). Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: krazy korn
directions: Boil together brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring often.
Take from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Stir until it foams high.
Pour over popcorn and stir to coat corn.

title: spicy apple twists
directions: Cut each apple into eight pieces.
Unroll crescent roll dough, separate into 8 triangles.
Cut each in half lengthwise to make 16 triangle strips.
Place
an apple piece at wide end of
each strip;
roll
up.
Arrange
in
9-inch
square
pan. Drizzle
with butter, sprinkle
with
mixture
of
sugar
and cinnamon.
Pour orange juice or water
into
pan, but not over dumplings.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm, plain or
with
cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet 'n sour pork
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, melt shortening.
Add pork steak.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Brown well.
Cover and cook for about 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese and 1 package Italian dressing mix. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours minimum.
Slice cucumbers 1/8-inch.
To serve, spread cheese mix on bread slice and top with cucumber.

title: greek chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in teriyaki sauce, garlic clove and lemons overnight.
Bake chicken at 350° for 45 minutes, then broil for 5 minutes to brown.

title: green chili roll-up
directions: Soften cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Add drained chilies and olives; mix well.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll tightly.
Slice 1 to 1 1/2-inches.
Chill and serve.

title: peggy's 1, 2, 3 bread
directions: Mix ingredients and place in well-greased loaf pan.
Let rise. Butter top and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cheese spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles. Brown ground beef; drain. Add onions, pepper and tomatoes; cook until tender and blended well. In large casserole, layer spaghetti and then meat mixture. Mix soup and milk; spread on top of meat mixture. Top with grated cheese. Repeat layers of spaghetti, meat sauce and cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes. Serve with Mexican cornbread.

title: southwest pork chops
directions: Brown meat and drain. Put in roasting pan and cover with all remaining ingredients. Bake slowly at 350° until the meat is very tender (coming off the bone). Check often and do not let these cook dry. You may have to add another 1/2 cup water if needed for sauce.

title: clarissa's cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Melt cheese and cheese soup, Accent, garlic salt, cumin, black pepper and Ro-Tel in microwave.
When melted, mix hamburger meat together.

title: warm brownie pudding cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch baking dish.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and 1/3 cup cocoa in medium bowl.
In a measuring cup, combine milk, butter and vanilla; stir into flour mixture and mix well.
Spoon batter into baking dish.

title: horseradish sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: blueberry nectarine crumble
directions: Mix nectarines, blueberries and lemon juice in an ungreased 3-quart baking dish. Spread evenly.
Mix oats, sugar, flour and spices. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until lightly browned at 350°.

title: broccoli and ritz casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain and spread in bottom of 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, onion, mayonnaise and eggs and pour over broccoli in the casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Casserole may be assembled ahead of time.

title: maraschino party cake
directions: Sift together in bowl flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add shortening, cherry juice, cherries and milk.
Beat vigorously with spoon for 2 minutes by clock (about 100 strokes per minute) or mix with electric mixer on slow to medium speed for 2 minutes.	Add egg whites; beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Pan size:
2 round layers, 8-inch diameter, and 1 1/4 deep (or 9-inch diameter, 1 1/2-inch deep).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: bungalosa (noodles)
directions: Mix flour, eggs, water and salt into a ball.
(May need to mix with hands.)
Cut with a knife into small pieces and put into boiling water.
Boil for 3 minutes and drain.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil the first 5 ingredients until soft ball stage.
Add last 2 ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour in buttered pan.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Work together with enough milk to make a stiff dough to roll out thin.
Leave to dry on both sides. Cut into strips and drop into boiling meat broth.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.

title: whipped margarine cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add salt and vanilla flavoring and blend until smooth. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo; blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 320° for about 45 minutes.

title: green goddess salad dressing(can also be used as a vegetable dip)
directions: Blend!
Store in refrigerator at least 2 hours before serving.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray the 16-inch pizza pan with Pam before placing the crescent rolls on as the crust, remembering to make a ridge all around the edge of the pan.
If using a smaller pizza pan, 1 can of crescent rolls may be enough to form the crust.
Brown sausage and drain on paper towels.
Layer sausage, hash browns and Cheddar cheese.
Mix beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over the rest and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grasshopper ice cream pie
directions: Grease micro-proof 9-inch pie plate.
In a micro-proof bowl, microwave 1/2 cup butter or oleo on High for 1 minute.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups graham cracker crumbs, 6 tablespoons cocoa and 1/3 cup confectioners sugar until well blended.
Press on bottom and up sides of prepared pie plate.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, until slightly blistered.
Do not overcook.
Cool completely.
Makes 1 chocolate pie crust.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Season chicken with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown in melted butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Drain chicken on paper towels; set aside.
Cook sausage, celery and onions in same skillet over medium-high heat until vegetables are tender, stirring frequently.
Add rice, corn and lemon juice; mix well.
Pour into buttered shallow baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top of rice mixture, pushing slightly into rice mixture.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package. Pour 1/2 batter into greased, floured 9 x 13 pan. Bake 15 min at 350 degrees. Melt caramels with milk and margarine over low heat. Pour over 1/2 baked layer. Top with chips and nuts and remaining batter. Bake 20 - 25 min. at 350 degrees

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 3 minutes.
Mix with remaining ingredients, then spread mixture in a 9-inch buttered pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding pineapple last and using only 1 cup of nuts.
Form into ball.
Roll in remaining nuts. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Place in a lightly greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese with sauce
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, layer macaroni and cheese, ending with cheese on top. Just before baking, pour milk over and spread bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: manicotti
directions: Pour 1 to 2 cups of sauce over bottom of large baking dish. Combine rest of ingredients and stuff shells with pastry tube. Pour remaining sauce over shells and top with a little grated Mozzarella.
Cover with foil and bake until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: recipe for a mom and dad
directions: Take the love and loyalty and mix with fate, understanding, tenderness and kindness. Add friendship, hope and forgiveness. Sprinkle with laughter and bake with sunshine. Serve daily.

title: 7-up apple dumplings
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients, stirring constantly, until all is dissolved. Set aside to cool.

title: candy cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil 1 minute.
Cool for a minute, then add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Press 1/2 nutmeat on center if preferred.

title: lemon curd mini tarts(makes 4 dozen)
directions: Place eggs and yolk in top of large double boiler.
Add sugar and whisk lightly to mix.
Add the butter, rind and juice.
Cook, uncovered, over moderate heat, stirring frequently, for 20 to 25 minutes or until mixture is as thick as heavy cream sauce. Strain.
Spoon into 4 dozen baked mini shells (recipe follows). Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Pipe or spoon on whipped cream.

title: potato-cheese puff
directions: Bring water, butter and salt to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in milk and potatoes. Cool slightly. Beat in eggs, Cheddar cheese and cayenne until well blended. Turn into well-greased 1-quart casserole. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes until golden and puffed.

title: filling for cakes or cupcakes
directions: Beat together and add to your cake (in the center).

title: doritos casserole
directions: Crush Doritos in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Brown ground beef; drain. Add soups, water and chilies.
Put beef mixture on top of crushed Doritos.
Put cheese on top and cook at 350° until lightly browned.

title: strawberry figs
directions: Combine sugar and figs.
Cook 20 minutes.
Add Jell-O and Sure-Jell.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in sterilized jars.

title: old-time tea cakes
directions: Make a stiff dough and work in flour until it is the right consistency to roll.
Roll thin and cut.
Bake at 300° or 350° until done.

title: p-nut butter cups
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
For filling, melt peanut butter with butter.
In small cupcake holder, cover bottom with chocolate. Spoon filing in middle.
Cover with chocolate.
Refrigerate.

title: light swiss mocha
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend on high for a few seconds until well mixed.
Allow dust to settle for several minutes before removing lid from container.
Store, tightly covered, in the refrigerator.

title: microwavable crispy oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix together egg, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger powder. Set aside.
On wax paper, mix together crushed corn flakes and onion.
Dip each wing in soy sauce mixture, then roll in corn flakes and onion.
In glass baking dish, cover and cook on High for 20 minutes.
Remove cover halfway through cooking time.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well; bring to boil in saucepan. Boil until it thickens; remove from heat.
Add the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir well; drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Let cool.

title: cake decorating vanilla icing
directions: Mix all
together
until
creamy and smooth.
May add a little extra
milk
if necessary.	Makes enough of icing for a large sheet cake or enough to decorate a pound cake.

title: crystallized pickles (sweet)
directions: You will need cheesecloth to tie pickling spices.

title: margot's garlic bread
directions: Rub entire outside of French bread with garlic clove.
Slice loaf lengthwise down the middle and cover with margarine. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley, then sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Place slices in a hot oven until crisp.

title: sweet 'n sour meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, egg, onion, bread crumbs, salt and pepper together.
Shape into 3/4-inch
meat balls. Place chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Place meat balls in the boiling mixture.
Be careful when turning meat balls so they will remain whole.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Poach chicken in broth for 20 minutes. Remove chicken from broth. Cool and cut into cubes. Mix soup and broth in pan over low heat. Add cream at very low heat to prevent curdling. When cream is thoroughly mixed, add sherry, stirring well. Place chicken cubes in buttered casserole. Add mushrooms and cooked spaghetti. Toss with sauce. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Grease and flour pan well.
Bake very thin, hot (400°) oven until brown.
This freezes well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: mashed potato salad
directions: Fix instant mashed potatoes according to package directions. Add mustard, sour cream and onions.
Is good both cold or hot. Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: dutch oven enchiladas
directions: Mix together chicken, onion, green pepper, and 1 can of chilies.
Fill tortillas with mixture and some cheese.
Roll up and place in lightly greased Dutch oven.
Mix together enchilada sauce, soup, and sour cream.
Pour over tortillas.
Top with remainder of grated cheese, olives, and chilies.
Cover and bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a waxed paper lined (9 x 13-inch) baking pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over this, then melted oleo over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and remove inverted from pan.
Remove wax paper.
(Cake mix will form bottom crust.)
Top with cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip (combine and spread over cooled pie).

title: upside-down rubble bubble cake
directions: Combine dates, 1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda and boiling water. Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening, white sugar and eggs; then add date mixture.
Stir in sifted flour, 3/4 teaspoon soda and salt.
Pour batter in greased pan.
Sprinkle topping of brown packed sugar, chocolate chips (regular size) and nuts over batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in oblong pan.

title: crunchy chocolate squares
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water, milk and chocolate morsels. Stir until smooth.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Stir until well blended.
Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 (1-inch) candies.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in bottom of 1 large cake pan and sprinkle seasoning packet over rice.
Lay chicken over the rice.

title: gluten cutlets
directions: Roll gluten slices in corn meal, vegetable salt and garlic mixture.
Brown in vegetable oil in frying pan until golden.
Place buttered cutlets in buttered baking pan.
Top with tomato soup. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mozzarella cheese can be added for a topping before tomato soup is added to casserole.
Like Veal Parmesan; yum!

title: pound cake
directions: Measure and sift plain flour 3 times (White Lily is best!). Keep the eggs at room temperature.
Mix butter and sugar well. Add eggs one at a time, beating them well.
Then add cream, flavoring and flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.
Preheat oven at 300°.

title: chicken wiggle
directions: Cook together onion with green pepper and pimento in a small amount of oil until tender.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes (or combine all in long casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes).

title: polish cooking is the best!
directions: Shred cabbage and place 1/2 in a large roasting pan.
Add sauerkraut, sliced kielbasa and remaining cabbage.
Pour tomato sauce on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with rye bread.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and add to vegetables in small saucepan.
Add enough water to barely cover vegetables.
Simmer, covered, until just tender.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour 1/2 batter into ungreased tube pan.
Place sliced apples on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar to taste.
Pour remaining batter in tube pan.
Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. (Toothpick test to check if done.)

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Press half of mixture in greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place rhubarb on top of crust.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla in a saucepan and cook until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb and top with the remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops and scalloped potatoes in crock-pot
directions: Put 1/2 of chops, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over the top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine; mix well.
Press around each cherry with stems out.
Combine chocolate and wax in a double-boiler.
Dip cherry balls in chocolate.
Place on wax paper and cool.

title: darlene's chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breasts and dice.
In a large mixing bowl, combine chicken with onion, celery, grapes and stir together with Hellmann's mayonnaise until good and moist.
You may also add chopped walnuts or pecans as another option.

title: raspberry tartlets
directions: Bake pastry shells in 8-inch round cake pans, following the package directions.
Melt preserves in 1-quart saucepan over low heat.
Spoon into pastry shells.
Top with 1/2 the whipped cream and the raspberries.
Garnish with remaining whipped cream.
Makes 2 servings.

title: rhubarb pie(my sisters, luella and loretta, both love rhubarb.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and flour.
Add egg, and mix well. Stir in rhubarb.
Place in Hot Water Crust.
Top with pats of butter and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine milk and beaten eggs in bowl, mixing well. Add lemon juice slowly, blending well. Pour in crust. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Add sugar and vanilla gradually, beating until blended. Spread over filling. Bake at 350° until brown. Chill until serving time.

title: super simple stew
directions: Stir-fry meat, onion, pepper and celery (use tenderizer on meat if necessary).
Add carrots, cabbage, potato and tomatoes.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add barley and basil.
Simmer until barley is tender.
Serve hot with salad and a simple dessert.

title: fat-free bread pudding
directions: Tear bread in small pieces and put in 2-quart baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Combine rest of ingredients except cinnamon. Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put dish into a 9 x 13-inch pan filled with 1 1/2 to 2 inches water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes (until knife inserted comes out clean).

title: mustard carrots
directions: Combine butter, mustard and sugar in skillet.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix for 5 minutes and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Test cake, you may have to bake a few minutes longer.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, Crisco and sugar together.
Add coloring and vanilla to milk and mix alternately with dry ingredients; add creamed mixture.
Mix and put into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can frost with favorite frosting.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
Rinse in cold water; drain.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, spices and mustard.
Mix well with rotini.
Add onion, tomato, cucumber, carrots and pimentos.
Toss and mix well.
Chill.

title: pate
directions: Cook the
liver
in a small amount of water.
Fry bacon with garlic
and
onion.
Add chopped hard egg, mushrooms and bay leaves and chicken cube.
Blend well.
Ready to eat.

title: christmas salad
directions: Boil cranberries, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Stir in 2 boxes of jello while mixture is hot.
To this add nuts, apples and celery.
Pour mixture into glass or Tupperware dish and chill until set firm.
Before serving, top with sour cream.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 1/8-inch thick strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef; toss and set aside.
Heat oil in large pan or wok.
Add beef and cook over high heat until browned. Cover and simmer 30 to 40 minutes over low heat.
Turn heat up; add vegetables and cook 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with water. Add to pan; stir and cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: kraut and beer cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and cocoa.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add sifted ingredients and beer to creamed mixture.
Fold in sauerkraut. Bake in greased and floured pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chewy cake squares
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add all other ingredients and pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry crunch cake
directions: Mix and press in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, pour in ovenproof bowl.
Mix flour, sugar, juice and pour over pineapple.
Top with cheese; cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with margarine; bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Can be made a day before serving.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Simmer 3 minutes and cool first three ingredients.
Add next four ingredients to cooled mixture.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rice and cheese.
In a separate bowl combine eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Add the two mixtures to spinach and pour into an oiled casserole or large pie plate. Mix wheat germ or bread crumbs with butter and spread on top. Bake 35 minutes or until set.
Serves 4.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put into top of double boiler brown sugar, flour and butter. Cook until butter melts.
Add milk, water, egg yolks and vanilla. Cook until thick.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: beef and sour cream casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
In Pyrex casserole, alternate layer of noodles, meat mixture and sour cream.
Repeat layers and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
Can be made ahead of time.
Serve with salad and bread.
Your meal is complete.

title: old-fashioned custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with bottom crust; flute edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken in tomato-vegetable sauce
directions: Sprinkle red pepper over chicken.
Brown chicken in olive oil on both sides.
Add onion and carrot.
Spread tomato paste on chicken.
Add wine and broth.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add clove of garlic.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add mushrooms and cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over linguini.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown lamb and onions.
Drain off excess grease.
Add beans and enchilada sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into sheet cake pan lined with tortillas.
Top with tortillas and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese is melted, 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and top with lettuce.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mince onion.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with a rounded loaf of bread.

title: tuna log
directions: Mix together all ingredients and chill 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and form into roll.
Roll in 1/2 cup chopped nuts (pecans).

title: lemon jello mix
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put pineapple juice in measuring cup and add water to make 1 cup; add to the first 4 ingredients. Bring to a good boiling point and boil for 5 minutes.
Mix jello mix with 1 cup hot water and 1 cup cold water and add boiling mixture to it.
Chill this until firm, then add the pineapple, bananas, marshmallows and nuts.
Top with off with 1 cup of whipped cream.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To prepare one serving, add 3 tablespoons of mix to 6 ounces of hot water.

title: chile verde con carne
directions: Partially freeze steak and cut in strips 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick. Combine flour and salt.
Dredge strips in flour and brown in oil in skillet.
Brown 1/3 of strips at a time; pour off drippings. Sprinkle meat with cumin and sugar.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Cut tomatoes into pieces and reserve.
Add tomato liquid, lemon juice and garlic to meat and stir.
Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Stir green pepper, onion, chiles, parsley and bouillon into meat mixture.
Cover tightly and cook slowly 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in reserve tomatoes.
Cook, covered, 15 minutes longer or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk together for 1 minute.
Remove from burner and add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper and cool.

title: larry's christmas bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine warm milk, sugar, salt and lemon rind in a bowl; mix well.
Cut butter into flour with a pastry blender in a large bowl until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yeast mixture and egg to milk mixture; mix well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place 1 hour and 15 minutes or until doubled.
Punch down.
Add raisins, cherries and almonds.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic.
Divide dough into 3 portions.
Roll each into 20-inch ropes.
Place side by side on greased baking sheet; braid.
Tuck ends under to seal. Cover, let rise 30 minutes or until doubled.
Brush top with 1 egg yolk and 1 tablespoon water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool and drizzle with glaze.

title: pink party punch
directions: In bowl, combine jello, Kool-Aid, sugar and hot water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add cold water and pineapple juice and stir to blend.
Chill or freeze.
(If you freeze the punch, thaw it enough before to leave it slushy.)

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide margarine and melt in two 9-inch cake pans.
Divide pineapple between the two pans, spreading with the back of a tablespoon.
Sprinkle half of the sugar in each pan, covering the pineapple.
Dot with additional margarine and set aside.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift the flour and salt into a basin.
Make a well in the center and crack the eggs into it.

With a wooden spoon gradually beat the egg and flour together, drawing the flour from the sides. Add some of the water if the mixture becomes too thick, beat until smooth, then stir the remainder of the water and then the milk into the mixture.
Alternatively, mix the ingredients, following the same sequence, in a food processor.

title: chopstick tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and water.
Add 1 cup chow mein noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Put into ungreased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles over top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Garnish with drained mandarin orange sections.

title: easy 'n sweet honey chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Melt butter in a frying pan; reduce heat enough so that butter doesn't burn.
Brown both sides of chicken pieces in a frying pan.
Arrange on a baking sheet (bone side up) and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Then flip the pieces and cover with honey.
Bake another 30 minutes at 350°; the drippings are so good you'll want to scoop them back on the chicken before serving.

title: syrian rice
directions: Fry orzo in butter until it is lightly browned.
Add rice; fry a little longer, until rice is glazed.
Add cold water to one inch over rice.
Cook to a slow boil, put lid on and simmer on very low flame.
Gently fold rice over and cook a little longer until rice is cooked.
Serves 6.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix ingredients in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pack in jars.
Process in water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in quarters.
In greased casserole, arrange a layer of tortillas and a layer of chopped, deboned chicken, olives, chilies and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix broth and soups and pour over mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until it is bubbly and starts to brown.
You may use chicken breast for better flavor and make it very spicy by using more chilies.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix ingredients well; add nuts last.
Make a small ball in hand and then press out shape of finger.
Cook in 225° oven for 1 hour.
Take out; let cool for 10 minutes and then roll in powdered sugar.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute bacon and onion together and drain.
Place sauerkraut in bottom of casserole (unwashed).
Add the macaroni curls, bacon, onion and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir gently. Bake 1/2 hour. Serves 4.

title: pronto potato soup
directions: In small frying pan,
brown
bacon until crisp.
Remove and let drain on paper towel.
Add
onion
to drippings in pan and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain
fat.	Meanwhile
in
3 quart saucepan, mix cold mashed potatoes and stir until smooth.
Add milk gradually to
desired	consistency,
stirring constantly. Add bacon and onions.
Season
with
salt, pepper and parsley. Heat through.
Yields 3 to 4 generous servings.

title: sunday pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and chopped walnuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip together; spread on cooled crust.
Mix the pudding and milk; pour into pan.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of the dessert.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in oleo.
When tender add soup and Velveeta cheese.
Dice chicken, cook noodles in chicken broth.
When noodles are tender, drain and add noodles and chicken to cheese mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While mixing dry ingredients, place butter in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Let it get sizzling hot.
Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Pour hot butter over mixture.
Mix well.
Press into same 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown on top.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients at one time until eggs are well mixed. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour or until cake begins to pull away from pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Cool and frost with Caramel Topping.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in 2-quart deep casserole.
Add seasoned salt and pepper (optional).
Mix 1 can of water with tomato soup and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Pour kidney beans (undrained) over top for last 10 minutes of baking.

title: easy mints
directions: Mix with hands. Roll in balls. Roll balls in granulated sugar. Flatten with hand and crisscross with fork for design.
If molds are used, press and flip out.
Freezes well.

title: aunt hulda's salad dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake.
Will keep a few months.

title: spaghetti in a pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir in margarine, cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture onto a crust in a 10-inch glass or microwavable pie plate.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 or 3 minutes or until set.

title: biscuits from scratch
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift together into mixing bowl.
Add shortening (unmelted; the colder the better).
Mix with flour thoroughly.
Make a "well" in mixture and add cold milk. Stir rapidly until soft dough is formed.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board and knead for 30 seconds.
