If dough becomes too sticky, dust lightly with flour.
Roll dough out half an inch thick for light, high biscuits; thinner for crusty biscuits.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits in lightly greased pan, brushing tops with melted shortening or cooking oil.
Let biscuits touch if you want them brown on top and bottom only. Place them a half inch apart if you want the sides lightly crusted.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in preheated 475° oven.

title: farmers salad
directions: Place ingredients in large bowl in layers with the first ingredient at the bottom.
Marinate in refrigerator for at least 5 hours or overnight.
Toss well just before serving.

title: onion barbecue glaze
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup mix, preserves, chili sauce and vinegar.
Use as glaze on steak, burgers, chops, chicken.
Brush on during last half of cooking.

title: pan enchiladas
directions: Heat together enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Layer as follows in 9 x 13-inch pan:

6 corn tortillas (dipped in the enchilada sauce), hamburger meat, rice, half of the cheese, 6 corn tortillas (no need to dip these), enchilada sauce and cheese. Cook in 425° oven until cheese melts and browns (approximately 30 to 40 minutes).

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Add water, chicken and carrots to 4-quart pan (cover).

Cook until chicken is done and carrots are tender. Add bouillon cubes, spices, potatoes, green beans and chicken soup. Cover and cook on medium heat for approximately 20 minutes. Add celery, onions and enough cabbage to fill pan.
Cover and cook on low heat approximately 30 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: fruit salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend ingredients together; shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 48 appetizers.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend and bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350° (grease and flour pan).

title: festive cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, sherry extract and onion, garlic and celery salts.
Blend until smooth. Add olives.
Cover and chill until firm.

title: delicious pork chop dish
directions: Brown pork chops and add sliced or diced bell pepper and onion.
Stir.
Add spices; mix well.
Add all the chicken broth; let simmer until done.

title: veggie sandwiches
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Beat egg and spread over crescent rolls.
Bake until light brown.
Mix together the mayonnaise, cream cheese and dressing mix until smooth.
Remove crescent rolls and let cool.
Grate vegetables and cheese.
When dough is cool, spread dressing mixture over dough, then sprinkle with vegetables and top with cheese.
Let chill overnight.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: pork chops and minute rice
directions: In separate bowl, place 1/4 cup fine, seasoned bread crumbs, 1/2 teaspoon paprika and 1 tablespoon margarine melted.
In medium pan, put rice, water, undrained corn, carrot, onion and thyme. Bring to a boil and stir in soup.
Put this in a rectangular baking dish.
Salt and pepper three or four pork chops.
Put these on top of rice mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove foil and sprinkle on bread crumbs. Cook until done.

title: cake top chocolate pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add vanilla and milk.
Set aside.
Mix well flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk mixture just to blend.
Pour into a deep, 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle evenly with remaining 1/2 cup cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour hot water over top.

title: lemon bars
directions: With pastry cutter, cut 2 cups flour with butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes (lightly brown).
Beat eggs, 2 cups sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, lemon juice and baking powder in bowl.
Pour over crust and bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: marian's scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn and milk.
Add eggs, crumbs and the other ingredients in mixing bowl.
Pour into well-greased casserole. Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Top with paprika, if desired.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together real well and refrigerate until firm.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat together until smooth.

title: moss ball
directions: Crumble Bleu cheese and add to grated Cheddar.
Add cream cheese and seasonings.
Form into a ball.
Roll in parsley and chill well before serving with crackers.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the rhubarb and sugar and spread on top of cake mix.
Pour whipping cream over the top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
May serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: crab scramble casserole
directions: Pour margarine into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch square casserole dish; tilt dish to coat bottom.
Beat eggs, milk, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Stir in crabmeat and cream cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Stir gently 2 to 3 times.
(At this point, you may cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Stir gently before baking.)
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, until center is set, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: beef pot hot soup
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion in butter; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for an hour and stir.

title: raspberry grilled chicken
directions: Place the chicken in a large glass baking dish.
Mix the vinegar, cranberry juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and black pepper; pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour, turning over after 30 minutes.

title: tuna rice and cheese bake
directions: Melt cheese in the milk; microwave or melt in a double boiler. Add tuna, flaked.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes, onion, soup, cheese, sour cream and melted margarine with salt and pepper.
Place in dish.
Crush corn flakes and mix with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Put on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: white veal scaloppine
directions: Dust cutlets with flour, shaking off excess.
Heat oil and 1 tablespoon of the butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add veal to hot butter in a single layer and cook until browned on both sides (about 1 to 2 minutes per side).
Remove and set aside.

title: potato - tomato bake
directions: In medium saucepan, blend the dry sauce mix from packaged potato mix with the tomato sauce, add the water and green pepper. Heat sauce mixture to boiling; add dried potatoes and stir till well combined.
Turn potato mixture into 1 1/2 qt. casserole. Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes or till potatoes are tender and heated through.
Sprinkle french fried onions over casserole and bake 3 minutes more or till onions are heated thorough.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into balls and bake in a 350° oven until brown.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup; add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid; cool.
Gently stir in ginger ale; chill until partially set.
Blend fruits; fold into gelatin.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish; chill until firm. Prepare topping according to package.
Blend in cheese; spread over gelatin.
Toast nuts in 1 tablespoon butter.

title: peanut butter cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased muffin tins.
Bake until done.

title: easy chicken pie(low fat)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix together vegetables, chicken, and soup in an ungreased pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients together with a fork until blended; pour over chicken mixture. Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: 7 up pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to 325° and have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Add flour alternately with 7-Up and flavoring.
Bake in well-greased tube or Bundt pan at 325° until done.
Needs no frosting.

title: pioneer cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg in bowl and add milk.
Melt margarine in iron skillet or baking pan.
Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Add dry ingredients to egg-milk mixture and mix well.
Add margarine and mix well.
Add honey or sugar, as desired. Bake 15 minutes or until almost done.
If done enough after 15 minutes, turn over in pan and finish baking and browning the top. (All ovens differ, so baking time may differ.)
Eat and enjoy.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in order into bowl.
Combine mayo and sugar; spread evenly over top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese and any leftover bacon bits.
Cover.
Refrigerate for 12 hours. Serve as is or mix first.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix sugar and butter until smooth. Melt chocolate and let cool.
Add cooled chocolate to sugar and butter mixture; blend until smooth. Add vanilla and cream of tartar, mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing well between each addition.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: crab or shrimp mold
directions: In top of double boiler, heat soup.
Stir in cheese and softened gelatin.
Stir frequently.
When ingredients are well blended, add other ingredients, mixing together.
Pour into greased mold.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with your favorite cracker or melba toast.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place diced chicken in a large baking dish.
Top with onion and cheese.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and cayenne pepper.
Crush 1/2 package of chips and place on top.
Mix in bowl the chicken and mushroom soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour over chicken and chips.
Crush remaining chips and place over casserole; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: In oblong baking dish, combine soup, water, rice, mushrooms and 1/2 can of onions.
Arrange chicken on rice mixture and sprinkle with paprika and pepper.
Bake at 375° until chicken is done.
Top with remaining onions and bake 3 more minutes until onions are golden brown.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: graham cracker refrigerator cookies
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, egg and milk until thickened.
Add graham cracker crumbs, pecans and coconut to the cooked mixture. Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Pour the cooked mixture over the crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers and frost while still warm.

title: mexican dish
directions: Spread refried beans in 9 x 13 baking dish. Add ground beef. Top with salsa and chilies. Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees. Add shredded cheddar
or taco cheese. Bake a few more minutes for the cheese to melt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients, except peanut butter, until mixture forms a ball by dropping small amount in a cup of water.
Place pan in sink of cold water.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Pour into buttered dish.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla extract and almond extract.
Add flour mixture.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies cereal, coconut, nuts and raisins.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls. Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove large stems from spinach leaves; tear leaves into bite-sized pieces.
Place in a large heatproof salad bowl.
Add mushrooms, eggs and cheese; set aside.
In a heavy 10-inch skillet, cook bacon slices until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon when cool enough to handle; place crumbled bacon in bowl with spinach.
Heat drippings over medium heat; whisk in mustard and sugar and whisk 1 minute.
Pour in vinegar; whisk until sugar dissolves.
Add salt and pepper.
Add olive oil in a slow, steady stream, whisking constantly.
Stir in green onions; immediately invert skillet over salad bowl.
Leave in place 1 minute to slightly wilt greens. Remove skillet; toss salad well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken stir fry
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Toss with 1 1/2 teaspoons soy sauce. Combine broth with cornstarch and remaining soy sauce.

Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet, add chicken strips and cook, stirring frequently until brown and cooked through, remove chicken. Add remaining oil to skillet, add vegetables. Stir fry over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add broth mixture.
Bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet.
Add walnuts and heat for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place asparagus in a flat baking dish.
Scatter with chopped eggs.
Add bacon and almonds.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Cover with soup and cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: chili stewed hen
directions: Saute onion and garlic; set aside.
Dust chicken with flour and brown on both sides.
Stir in onion, garlic mixture, chili puree, bay leaves, oregano, thyme, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Remove bay leaves.
In a small bowl, blend cornstarch and water until smooth.
Combine with mixture in skillet and cook over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken.
See recipe for Red Chili Puree.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the first five ingredients and stir well.
Stir in the eggs, but do not beat.
Fold in pecans.
Pour into pastry-lined pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar; let stand overnight.
Next morning, add the celery, nuts and jello-hot water.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In 5-quart kettle, over medium heat, heat oil.
Add onion, celery and garlic; saute 2 minutes, or until onion is limp.
Stir in bouillon cubes, water and tomatoes with their liquid, crushing tomatoes into small pieces.
Over high heat, add carrots, cauliflorets, lima beans, marjoram leaves, thyme leaves and pepper.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add pasta to soup; cook, covered, for 15 minutes longer.
Before serving, sprinkle with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: macaroni 'n casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package until tender, but not soft.
Chop pimento, onion and cheese.
Combine all ingredients while macaroni is hot.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in freezer.
Stir after 8 to 12 hours.
Stir occasionally.
When ready to serve, add one 2 liter bottle diet 7-Up.

title: pineapple nut ball
directions: Combine cheese, 1 cup nuts, pineapple, peppers, onion and salt; mix well and chill one hour.
Divide mixture in half. Shape each into ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Chill several hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers.
Yields two 3-inch balls.

title: mexican meatloaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a loaf pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Then add flour, baking powder and milk.
Then add fruit that has been chopped up and dredged with a little extra flour.
Add nuts, coconut, flavoring and lemon juice.
Put in greased pans lined with greased paper and bake at 300° for about 3 hours or until done.
Size of pan will govern time.

title: chinese cabbage soup
directions: Brown ginger in oil until brown.
Remove ginger and discard. Wash and cut cabbage in 1-inch lengths.
Add to oil with broth, mushrooms, chicken and black pepper. Cover.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 to 6 minutes.
I like a lot of black pepper.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cut into 8 servings.
Refrigerate overnight.
Flour pieces and fry in oleo.
Place meat in baking dish.
Cover with 1 can mushroom soup and gravy drippings.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until combined.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour and 1 cup of potato chips; cover and chill dough for 2 or 3 hours.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining crushed potato chips. Place balls 1-inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten until about 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer onto foil to cool.
Makes about 20.

title: biscuit mix
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Toss oil thoroughly with mixture.
Store in a cool place.
Will keep 2 to 3 weeks on trail conditions or 3 months in home refrigerator.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Store in a cool, dry place.

title: paprika shrimp
directions: Chop onion and slice mushrooms.
In a large skillet, melt butter over moderately high heat.
Add shrimp and saute until they turn pink, about 2 minutes.
Transfer the shrimp to a bowl and set it aside.

title: delicious beets
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and thicken with cornstarch. Serves 6.
Good with holiday fare.

title: sweet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: cream cheese swirl coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, beat cheese, confectioners sugar and lemon juice until smooth.
Set aside. Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat granulated sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream; mix well.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Spoon cheese mixture on top of batter to within 1/2 inch of pan edge.
Spoon remaining batter over filling, spreading to pan edge.
Sprinkle with Cinnamon-nut Topping.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve warm.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Throw all in a big pot and cook all morning or until meat is done.

title: anchovy spread
directions: Put all ingredients except cream cheese into blender container. Cover.
Press button 7 for 10 seconds.
With motor running on speed 7, drop cut-up cheese into opening at top.
Continue blending until smooth.
Stop to push down with spatula if needed.

title: barbecups
directions: Mix ground beef, barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar; mix well.
Take the biscuits, press each into ungreased muffin cups, making sure dough goes up to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups and sprinkle with the cheese on top of cups.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 12 cups.

title: alden family punch
directions: Add approximately 1/2 amount of water to canned juices.
Add 1/2 amount of water to fruit punch.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes into a pot of water and boil for 25 to 30 minutes or until done. Add salt, pepper, onion, milk, cheese, flour and sour cream; cook for 10 to 15 more minutes or until onions become clear.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add all other ingredients (do not drain).
I added about 1 cup shredded cabbage, but not necessary. Heat slowly.
Serve with Broccoli Cornbread.

title: banana bran muffins(cinnamon topped)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla.
Add cereal and let stand 5 minutes. Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend into banana-brand mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured muffin pan
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: aunt annie bailey's chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa.
Add beaten egg yolks and then butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Spread over pie and brown.

title: moo shu pork
directions: Makes filling for 8 (6-inch) Chinese pancakes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups broth. Cool, debone and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a long baking dish, layer chicken, eggs, carrots and peas.
Spread undiluted soup over this.
Pour the 2 cups of broth over layers. Melt margarine in a small bowl.
Stir in flour, then milk.
(Will have some small lumps.)
Spoon this over the layers in the baking dish.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until golden brown.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with enough vinegar to make of creamy consistency.
Pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add onion slices.
Serve.
Additional cucumbers and onions may be added to remaining dressing.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar. Add 2 eggs and 1/4 cup milk. Mix with mixer. Add flour, powder, soda, salt and vanilla; mix well. Cover and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board approximately 3/4-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° for less than 10 minutes until lightly brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, margarine and water.
Press into an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Prick several times. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together to use with raw vegetables.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir the sugar, water and cornstarch all together; boil for 3 minutes until clear.
Add the jello to the mixture while hot.
Add coloring to make desired color; let cool.
Pour the strawberries into the cooled mixture.
Let stand until set.
Stir and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with hands.
After mixing, refrigerate until firm.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Wrap loosely in foil.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place one piece of dried beef under each chicken breast.
Wrap with a piece of bacon.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put on a small amount of sour cream.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: granny byrum's chicken stew
directions: Put chicken in large pot; pour in about 3 quarts of water. Cook about 45 minutes until chicken is done.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Mix meal and flour in large glass.
Finish filling glass with water; stir well.
Pour this into boiling chicken broth.
Cook until this thickens slightly.
Remove from heat.
Put chicken back in pot or pick chicken off the bone, then stir in pot of stew. Serve with cornbread.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans; press into a pan.
Bake until lightly browned.
Beat cream cheese, Cool Whip (1 cup) and sugar and spread over crust.
Prepare pudding mix and layer over cream cheese mix.
Then spread Cool Whip over the top.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Chill and serve.

title: granola cereal
directions: Mix all of the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
In a saucepan,
combine honey, oil, vanilla and orange rind.
Heat until warmed.
Pour the honey mixture over dry ingredients in bowl.
Stir until coated.
Pour this mixture into broiler pan or large jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15
minutes, until golden brown.
Cool; stir in raisins.
Store in covered jar.
Eat plain or with milk.

title: beer cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy-duty zip top plastic bag. Push air out of bag and seal.
Knead bag with hands until mixture is blended and of spreading consistency.
Serve with bagel chips. Yields 2 1/4 cups.

title: crispy crab
directions: Mix the cheese, margarine, crab and garlic.
Spread on the English muffin halves; freeze.
When ready to use, cut each half into 1/8; bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: raw artichoke and mushroom salad
directions: Squeeze lemons into a small bowl.
Set aside.
Pull off tough outer leaves from artichokes and discard.
Trim bottoms and tops. Slice lengthwise and pull out the fuzzy choke, if any.
Slice artichokes crosswise as thinly as possible and immediately place in lemon juice to prevent browning.
Slice mushrooms.
Remove artichokes from lemon juice with a slotted spoon.
Combine with mushrooms and dress with olive oil, salt and pepper.
Toss with half of the Parmesan and arrange on 4 salad plates.
Garnish with remaining cheese and serve.

title: o'charley's caramel pie
directions: Set cans in pan deep enough to be over cans, 1 to 2-inches. Pour very hot water over cans and bring to a boil.	As water boils out pour hot water in and keep cans covered with water at all times.
Boil 3 hours.
Be very careful.
Set aside and cool at least 2 hours.
When opening cans be very careful, only puncture at first.
Stand back, it may spurt out!

title: buffet lasagne
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic in a large skillet; pour off excess fat.
Add salt, oregano, basil, pepper, tomato paste and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes; meanwhile, cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together butter, peanut butter and sugars with electric mixer.
Add egg and continue to mix.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Press a Hershey's Kiss in each cookie.
Return to oven for 5 to 6 more minutes.
Cool.

title: chili beans
directions: Combine gravy, tomatoes and chili powder in pot. Bring to a boil, then stir in beans and chilies.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Top with a combination of sour cream, green onions and cheese.

title: missionary pie
directions: Melt margarine in
pan. Mix together remaining ingredients (except fruit). Pour into 8x8 pan. Top with fruit.

title: dianne's coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Mix coconut, Pet milk and sugar; if needed, add 1 to 2 cups additional milk.
Cook on medium to low heat until not watery.
Add sugar to taste.
Stir occasionally while cooking to prevent sticking.
Pour just enough batter in round cake pan to cover pan, then bake until brown at 350°.
Recipe will make 6 to 8 layers.
Watch closely because it will cook within 5 to 8 minutes.
Punch holes in layers to allow juice to soak in.
Top with cooked coconut while still hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes after peeling just until fork can go in.
Cool and shred.
Combine cheese and butter; heat until melted.
Blend in sour cream.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan (greased).
Can be frozen for later use or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to simmering point and add salt.
Peel potatoes and cut into eighths.
Add potatoes, onion and leeks to broth.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Mash potatoes into the broth, using a potato masher to form smaller pieces of potato. Add chervil, parsley and whipping cream.
Simmer 5 more minutes; add butter and serve hot.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix with 5 or
cups flour to make fairly stiff dough; cover and refrigerate.
Pinch
off
dough
and make into rolls. Let rise and bake
at 425° for about 12 minutes or until brown. Roll dough will keep nicely in refrigerator for 4 or 5 days.

title: sunrise cherry pie
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine softened cream cheese, vanilla and 2 tablespoons juice, mixing well.
Stir in 1/4 cup pineapple and 1/2 cup pie filling. Gradually add sugar to cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Top with remaining pineapple around top and edges.
Pour remaining pie filling in center of pie.
Chill overnight.
(You may put layer of bananas on bottom of crust first, then add filling.)

title: crispy baked veggies
directions: Wash and pat dry vegetables.
Prepare (cut) and rinse; pat dry. Dip veggies into beaten egg.
In medium box combine butter, garlic, Parmesan cheese and potato flakes.
Roll dipped veggies in potato mixture.
Turn to coat all sides.
Place 1 inch apart onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly golden and crisp.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Bake in Bundt pan (Teflon lined) at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, using coarse blade.
Put in bag or colander and let stand and drain overnight.
The next day, grind together remaining ingredients, except flour, vinegar and water.
Add drained tomato mixture and enough vinegar to cover and bring to a boil.

title: banana sour cream bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and bananas well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add alternately to banana mixture with sour cream.
Stir to blend.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour bottom of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or 2 smaller pans and bake at 350° for about 60 to 75 minutes, less time for smaller pans.
Remove from pans and cool.
Wrap in plastic or foil to store.
Bread is better if allowed to stand, covered, overnight before cutting.
Can be frozen, then thawed for unexpected guests.
Tastes great spread with softened cream cheese.

title: squash souffle
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add flour. Gradually add milk and cook until sauce is thick.
Add small amounts of sauce to beaten egg until egg is temperature of sauce. Combine with remaining sauce. Mix squash and cheese into sauce until well bended while stirring over low heat.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Dot with pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 and freezes well.

title: oatmeal coconut pie
directions: Mix and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: vegetable stew
directions: In a stew pot, begin to saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add celery, carrots, eggplant, potatoes and sweet potato.

title: chicken pineapple apricot
directions: Place chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt to taste.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook butter, brown sugar, syrup and salt in microwave for 4 minutes.

After you've stirred well, add baking soda and vanilla. Mix well and pour immediately over popcorn in a large paper bag. Shake this, then cook in microwave for 1 minute and 35 seconds. Shake again; cook another 1 minute and 20 seconds.
Shake, pour into cake pan to cool and then break apart.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds, blanch in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain.
Brown turkey, onions and oregano.
Stir in rice, Parmesan, eggs and 1/2 cup tomato sauce. Stuff in peppers.
Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining tomato sauce.
Microwave 12 minutes.
Rearrange peppers once during cooking.
Serves 4.

title: white bean soup
directions: Cook beans, carrots and celery until done.
Add cream of chicken soup, can of broth, 2 tablespoons parsley and black pepper.
Cook in crock-pot until ready to serve.

title: sweet 'n spicy barbecued chicken
directions: Dip chicken in mixture of water and vinegar.
Grill about 6 inches from heat, turning frequently, about 50 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking soda and spices.
In a second bowl or food processor, cream the butter, sugar, orange rind and egg.
Combine the dry ingredients with the creamed mixture. Lightly mix in the persimmon pulp.
Drop the batter by the tablespoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with anise seed and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over rolled oats.
Let stand 20 minutes. Mix together sugars, shortening and eggs.
Sift flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Mix alternately with rolled oats and add to mixture.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed; add sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Bake in 3 layers or oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except the nuts and cherries.
Decorate the mixture with the nuts and cherries.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening.
Mix with sugar; add beaten eggs and applesauce.
Add applesauce mixture to dry ingredients; add nuts.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mom's corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat eggs together with milk and melted butter.
Add to corn mixture.
Mix well. Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Chill.
Keeps indefinitely in covered container in refrigerator.
Great served with raw veggies (broccoli and cauliflower florets, carrot and zucchini sticks, sliced mushrooms, radishes, cherry tomatoes, etc.).

title: crab dip
directions: Blend cream and cream cheese.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat until creamy.
Fold in crab meat.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover for 10 minutes or until done.
Serve with corn chips.

title: texas special
directions: Mix until crumbly.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° 15 minutes; cool.

title: chex muddy buddies or puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal into very large bowl.
Combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in 1-quart bowl and microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in vanilla.

title: potato, spinach, tomato soup
directions: In a deep pot, saute the oil, garlic, onion for 2-3 minutes. Add in broth and bring to a boil.
Add sliced potatoes, cook for 20 minutes and stir occasionally.
Potatoes will begin to break up and thicken the soup.
Stir in spinach in bunches, when one bunch wilts add another bunch.
Add nutmeg, salt, and pepper to taste. Stir in the tomatoes and heat through for 2-3 minutes.
Remove from heat to large serving bowl and add in grated cheese. Serves 4.

title: chocolate raspberry cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate chip morsels.
Spread batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: mud burgers
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook for 2 hours, first hour with foil.

title: party chicken
directions: Halve breast; wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each half.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan with chipped beef.
Arrange chicken on top.
Blend soup and sour cream and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika.
(May refrigerate at this point, if desired.)
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 pan in oven. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries over top, press gently.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to measure 1 1/4 cups.
Make cake batter as directed on package, except use pineapple juice mixture instead of water.
Pour batter over pineapple and cherries.
Bake 42-47 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
After cooked, immediately turn pan upside down on a heatproof serving plate.
Serve warm or cool.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil in the blender, add everything else.
Blend until all is very finely chopped.
Now add and mix in the cheese.
Use 1/2 cup per round of spaghetti.
You can also freeze it covered with 3/4-inch of olive oil.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill very thoroughly before serving.

title: rocky's meat marinade
directions: Mix all together. This is good for chicken or beef.
One hour or so for chicken and 2 to 4 hours for beef.

title: easy-mix candy
directions: Heat margarine in milk over low heat until margarine melts and mixture just begins to simmer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in dry frosting mix.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly with rubber scraper, until smooth and glossy, 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts, if desired, and either pour into aluminum foil lined loaf pan or drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
If necessary, reheat mixture slightly.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix well and spread over cake while cake is hot.

title: yellow jello salad
directions: Take jello and add boiling water, cold water, marshmallows, pineapple (not juice) and bananas.
Put in an 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish and set firm, several hours or overnight.
Take juice from pineapple and add water to make 1 cup.
Cook juice with sugar, flour and butter.
Add beaten egg.
Cook until thickened. Let cool.
Pour over jello and let get firm in refrigerator.

title: great chicken
directions: Put chicken in shallow, oblong glass baking dish.
Top each with a slice of cheese.
Mix soup and wine (or water) together and pour over chicken.
Partly crush the stuffing mix and scatter over the chicken.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except vanilla.
Cook slow until it forms a firm ball.
Beat until it has a creamy look.
Add vanilla.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms after removing stems. Cook onion in a small amount of butter or oil until transparent.
Set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a bowl, combine flour and sugar and cut butter in with a pastry blender.
Mixture will be dry and crumbly.
Spread flour mixture evenly over apples and pat down gently.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken delight
directions: Wash chicken and be sure chicken is plucked good.
Peel potatoes and quarter up.
Place potatoes around chicken.
Pour soup over chicken and add water.
Sprinkle pepper over top.
Place a lid on.
Pop in the oven.
Bake in 425° oven for 1 hour or until chicken gets golden brown all over.

title: four cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Combine noodles and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; top with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Bake for 5 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: roast style brisket
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Blend soy sauce with flour in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart Dutch oven. Add beef to soy sauce mixture and toss to coat meat. Add carrots, onions, celery, garlic, pepper, marjoram, thyme and wine to meat. Stir gently to mix. Cover tightly and bake
1 hour. Add mushrooms; stir gently, cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours longer or until meat and vegetables are tender. Serve with rice, noodles, hot biscuits or potatoes, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot balls
directions: Using equal parts of apricots and walnuts, run through food grinder.
Shape into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Makes 25.

title: glazed chicken wings
directions: Bake chicken wings in hot 400° oven 50 minutes.

title: zippy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer gently for 12 to 15 minutes.
I normally double this recipe.
This will keep in the refrigerator for months.

title: dump cake
directions: Put fruit and juice in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Cut oleo into thin slices and lay evenly on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cheese ball
directions: Knead ingredients together.
Form into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Top with cherry.

title: nita's ham rolls
directions: Take dinner rolls and slice them in half.
Mix next 5 of the ingredients together and brush on the rolls.
Then put on ham and Swiss cheese.
Place in the oven at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave until the cheese is melted 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
These are great to make ahead of time, freeze and then take out and cook.

title: yellow cabbage salad for large group
directions: Combine all the vegetables.
Heat to boiling all remaining ingredients.
Pour hot sauce over vegetables.
Keeps well.

title: dandy candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in mixing bowl. Add shortening, milk and vanilla. Beat 1 1/2 minutes on low speed. Add egg whites and beat 1 1/2 minutes.

Pour into a 9x9x2 inch pan, well greased and lightly floured on the bottom. Prepare the Dandy topping. Combine 1/4 c. flour and brown sugar. Cut in 1/4 c. butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in 1/2 c. flaked coconut and 1 1/2 tsp. lemon juice.
Sprinkle Dandy topping over batter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut together and sprinkle on bottom of buttered cake pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Pour on top of pecan and coconut mixture.
Mix together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar and drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Saute garlic and onion.
Place sliced zucchini in pan.
Cover 20 minutes.
Cover with Jack cheese and then cover for 3 minutes. Serve immediately.
